in%20the%20words%20of%20the%20author%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Econtributes%20to%20the%20violence%20to%20animals%2C%20a%20gendered%2C%20racist%2C%20anthropocentric%2C%20neutralization%20of%20harms%20intrinsic%20in%20dairying%E2%80%99.%20%3C%2Fem%3EThrough%20research%20in%20sites%20of%20cow%20production%20and%20protection%2C%20she%20sets%20out%20to%20politicise%20milk%20over%20the%20unfolding%20305%20pages%2C%20which%20she%20asserts%20will%20force%20us%20as%20humans%20to%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Econsider%20the%20living%20lactating%20animals%20vulnerability%20as%20a%20dairy%20resource%2C%20as%20well%20as%20those%20of%20racialized%20humans%20entrapped%20in%20specific%20segments%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20milk%20production.%20%3C%2Fem%3EWhilst%20flagging%20the%20necessity%20of%20the%20Hindu%20State%20to%20constantly%20create%20internal%20enemies%2C%20which%20translates%20into%20racial%2C%20casteist%20and%20fascist%20violence%20against%20Dalits%20and%20Muslims%2C%20marked%20and%20othered%20for%20ostensibly%20being%20%E2%80%98anti-cow%E2%80%99%2C%20because%20they%20eat%20beef%2C%20she%20describes%20how%20parallelly%20violence%20is%20unleashed%20against%20bovines%20in%20animal%20agriculture.%20She%20unpacks%20and%20explores%20cow%20protectionism%20by%20framing%20cows%20and%20buffaloes%20as%20political%20subjects%20and%20not%20objects%20of%20political%20analysis.%C2%A0%20Herein%20she%20stresses%20on%20the%20political%20nature%20of%20human-animal%20hierarchies%20and%20relations%2C%20and%20introduces%20anthropocentrism%20to%20the%20political%20analysis%20on%20cow%20protection.%20Narayanan%20argues%20that%20her%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Epoliticised%20multispecies%20ethnography%20is%20also%20an%20anti-caste%20methodology%2C%20and%20a%20plea%20to%20all%20caste%20groups%20to%20engage%20seriously%20with%20the%20decommodification%20of%20animals%20to%20undo%20the%20violence%20of%20anthropocentrism%2C%20as%20a%20necessary%20precursor%20to%20dismantle%20caste.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENarayanan%2C%20in%20her%20first%20chapter%2C%20outlines%20the%20continuum%20between%20India%E2%80%99s%20milk%20and%20beef%20economies%2C%20and%20how%20beef%20and%20other%20post-slaughter%20products%20are%20byproducts%20of%20dairying.%20She%20denounces%20the%20resounding%20silence%20across%20Indian%20politics%2C%20dairy%20and%20beef%20sectors%20about%20the%20veal%20industry%2C%20which%20is%20the%20flesh%20of%20discarded%20male%20calves%20separated%20from%20their%20dairy%20mothers%20at%20birth.%20She%20discusses%20the%20centrality%20of%20the%20cow%20to%20all%20forms%20of%20Indian%20nationalism%20%E2%80%93%20Hindutva%2C%20Congress%20or%20Development%20Nationalism%2C%20facilitated%20by%20the%20internal%20contradiction%20of%20Article%2048%20of%20the%20directive%20principles%20of%20state%20policy%2C%20which%20guided%20states%20to%20promote%20scientific%20breeding%20of%20bovines%20whilst%20prohibiting%20their%20slaughter.%20This%20reflected%20the%20impossible%20endeavour%20of%20a%20newly%20independent%20India%20to%20mediate%20secular%20democratic%20and%20Hindutva%20nationalism%2C%20with%20false%20promises%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98slaughter%20free%E2%80%99%20dairy%20industry.%20It%20also%20was%20an%20early%20victory%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20right%20to%20use%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20self-sacrificing%20mother%20cow%2C%20and%20the%20anti-slaughter%20clause%20therein%2C%20to%20advance%20their%20vision%20of%20restoring%20a%20supposed%20%E2%80%98pre-Islamic%E2%80%99%20pure%20Hindu%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cow%20was%20no%20less%20significant%20for%20Congress%20nationalism%2C%20with%20the%20latter%20equating%20cow%20protection%20to%20the%20defence%20of%20India%2C%20and%20associating%20cow%20milk%20with%20the%20purity%20of%20the%20nation.%20She%20concludes%20the%20chapter%20discussing%20the%20importance%20of%20dairying%20in%20the%20project%20of%20post-colonial%20nation%20building%2C%20for%20which%20Article%2048%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20breeding%20clause%20became%20critical%2C%20via%20which%20the%20bodies%20of%20cows%20and%20buffaloes%20experienced%20the%20most%20extractive%20forms%20of%20commodification.%20She%20traces%20how%20scientific%20breeding%20technologies%20to%20promote%20high-yielding%20Jersey%20and%20Holstein%20Friesan%20dairy%20breeds%2C%20have%20been%20central%20India%E2%80%99s%20White%20Revolution%2C%20which%20simultaneously%20unleashed%20huge%20violence%20upon%20animals%2C%20particularly%20the%20unwanted%2C%20unproductive%20and%20dry%20%E2%80%98foreign%20cows%E2%80%99%20and%20their%20male%20calves%2C%20hugely%20vulnerable%20to%20illegal%20trafficking%20and%20slaughter.%20Through%20subsequent%20chapters%20she%20vividly%20discusses%20the%20cow%2Fbuffalo%20subsidisation%20of%20milk%20production%20and%20the%20making%20of%20Secular%2FHindu%20India%2C%20within%20the%20contested%20context%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eutilization%20of%20the%20cow%20as%20an%20economic%20resource%20for%20Secular%20India%20which%20demands%20her%20slaughter%2C%20against%20the%20instrumentalization%20of%20the%20cow%20as%20a%20political%20resource%20for%20a%20Hindu%20India%20which%20demands%20the%20maintenance%20of%20her%20life%2C%20through%20the%20enforced%20labour%20of%20their%20bodies%20and%20disruption%20of%20their%20family%20bonds%E2%80%99.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20402px)%2085vw%2C%20402px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15113823%2FMother-Cow-Mother-India%25E2%2580%25949788195838530%25E2%2580%2594front%25E2%2580%2594Navayana.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15113823%2FMother-Cow-Mother-India%25E2%2580%25949788195838530%25E2%2580%2594front%25E2%2580%2594Navayana.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15113823%2FMother-Cow-Mother-India%25E2%2580%25949788195838530%25E2%2580%2594front%25E2%2580%2594Navayana-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15113823%2FMother-Cow-Mother-India%25E2%2580%25949788195838530%25E2%2580%2594front%25E2%2580%2594Navayana-683x1024.jpg%20683w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673144%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22603%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EYamini%20Narayanan%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EMother%20Cow%2C%20Mother%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ENayavana%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20chapter%202%2C%20the%20author%20describes%20the%20extreme%20violence%2C%20suffering%20and%20distress%20experienced%20by%20bulls%20milked%20for%20their%20semen%20which%20is%20frozen%2C%20and%20used%20to%20artificially%20inseminate%20dairy%20cows%2C%20a%20core%20activity%20in%20the%20scientific%20breeding%20of%20cows.%20She%20draws%20heavily%20from%20similar%20research%20of%20dairy%20industries%20located%20in%20the%20global%20north%2C%20to%20demonstrate%20how%20scientific%20breeding%20is%20replete%20with%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98gendered%20commodification%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Esexualized%20violence%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E.%20There%20is%20a%20caste%20system%20across%20bovines%2C%20where%20the%20sacrality%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20humped%20Indian%20cattle%20breeds%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Edisgust%2C%20loathing%2C%20and%20stigmatization%20of%20buffaloes%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20akin%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20%E2%80%98untouchability%E2%80%99%20in%20humans.%20These%20are%20historically%20related%20to%20power%20struggles%20between%20groups%3A%20the%20buffalo%20was%20regarded%20as%20sacred%20by%20the%20peoples%20of%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20civilisation%2C%20and%20the%20settler%20pastoralists%20and%20their%20cows%20eventually%20became%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%20castes%E2%80%99%2C%20with%20the%20sacrality%20of%20the%20cow%20gradually%20and%20firmly%20being%20established%20in%20Brahminical%20doctrine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20flags%20how%20scientific%20breeding%20has%20contributed%20to%20intensification%20of%20casteised%20speciesism%20very%20evident%20in%20the%20sites%20of%20cow%20protection%3A%20cow%20worshippers%20and%20vigilantes%2C%20worship%20the%20traditional%20purebred%20humped%20Indian%20cow%20breeds%20as%20the%20sacred%20mother%20goddess.%20Crossbred%20Jerseys%20and%20Holsteins%20are%20mere%20%E2%80%98animals%E2%80%99%2C%20shunned%20as%20%E2%80%98unholy%E2%80%99%20by%20Hindus%2C%20and%20the%20buffalo%2C%20which%20is%20ironically%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20commercially%20valuable%20animal%2C%20treated%20with%20utter%20contempt.%20This%20casteist%20perception%20of%20animals%20is%20used%20to%20justify%20violent%20factory%20farming%20dairy%20practices%20such%20as%20separation%20of%20calves%20from%20their%20mothers%20at%20birth%20and%20forbidding%20them%20to%20suckle.%20New%20breeding%20technologies%20such%20as%20semen%20sexing%2C%20to%20completely%20erase%20the%20population%20of%20%E2%80%98unwanted%20male%20calves%E2%80%99%2C%20advocated%20by%20animal%20welfare%20activists%20as%20a%20win-win%20situation%20for%20humans%20and%20animals%2C%20is%20mere%20%E2%80%98humane-washing%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Milking%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20title%20of%20chapter%203%2C%20dwells%20on%20the%20violence%20and%20cruelty%20associated%20with%20birthing%20and%20the%20separation%20of%20mother%20and%20calf%20which%20is%20intrinsic%20to%20industrial%20dairying%2C%20the%20resultant%20emotional%20trauma%20of%20mother%20cows%20and%20buffaloes%2C%20the%20starvation%20and%20slow%20painful%20death%20of%20calves%20if%20male%2C%20the%20tortuous%20milking%20by%20milk%20machines%20and%20the%20susceptibility%20of%20high-yielding%20dairy%20breeds%20to%20chronic%20mastitis%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20disallowing%20calves%20to%20suckle%20their%20mothers.%20Increasing%20incidence%20of%20mastitis%20and%20reproductive%20diseases%20in%20dairy%20animals%20translates%20to%20a%20stream%20of%20discarded%20bovines%20let%20out%20onto%20the%20streets%2C%20subjected%20to%20cruelty%20and%20finally%20slaughtered.%20The%20viciousness%20continues%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20peri-urban%20dairies%20where%20animals%20are%20intensively%20confined%20in%20completely%20unliveable%20conditions%2C%20the%20illegal%20dairy%20use%20of%20oxytocin%20to%20milk%20every%20last%20ounce%20of%20milk%2C%20the%20cruelty%20of%20forcing%20out%20non-productive%20cows%20onto%20the%20street%2C%20and%20the%20violence%20against%20these%20abandoned%20%E2%80%98strays%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20they%20survive%20consuming%20toxic%20plastics%20from%20urban%20garbage%20heaps%2C%20resulting%20in%20painful%20deaths.%20Narayanan%20brilliantly%20discusses%20how%20Hindu%20culture%20and%20its%20myths%20of%20Kamadhenu%20%E2%80%93%20the%20mythological%20cow%20with%20her%20exhaustless%20udder%20and%20streams%20of%20pure%2C%20heavenly%20milk%2C%20worshipped%20and%20revered%20as%20mother%2C%20seamlessly%20masks%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20living%20dairy%20cow%E2%80%99s%20motherhood%20%E2%80%93%20with%20her%20starving%20calf%20straining%20to%20reach%20her%20full%20udder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENarayanan%20moves%20to%20the%20sites%20of%20protection%20where%20in%20chapter%204%20she%20unpacks%20how%20gaushalas%20are%20actually%20sanctuaries%20for%20the%20cow-mother-nation%2C%20where%20the%20body%20of%20the%20dairy%20cow%20which%20invariably%20in%20gaushalas%2C%20is%20the%20indigenous%20cow%20breed%20(as%20gaushalas%20reject%20Jerseys%20and%20Holstein%20cows)%2C%20is%20above%20all%20a%20Hindu%20State.%20A%20piercing%20example%20she%20describes%20is%20the%20cruelty%20of%20intensive%20dairy%20production%20being%C2%A0%20protected%20and%20supported%20in%20the%20name%20of%20devotion%20via%20Hindu%20rituals%20and%20belief%20systems%20where%20dairy%20farmers%2C%20most%20of%20them%20small%20scale%2C%20donate%20their%20discarded%20male%20calves%20to%20temples.%20The%20act%20of%20this%20being%20an%20offering%20to%20god%2C%20allows%20them%20to%20assuage%20their%20conscience%20of%20separating%20calves%20from%20their%20mothers%2C%20and%20the%20inevitability%20of%20slaughter%20that%20awaits%20the%20calf%2C%20as%20they%20can%20leave%20the%20fate%20or%20karma%20of%20the%20calf%20%E2%80%98%20to%20god%E2%80%99.%20She%20describes%20how%20the%20top%20brass%20of%20temples%20and%20gaushalas%2C%20as%20also%20Hindu%20milk%20consumer-devotees%2C%20who%20are%20in%20complete%20denial%20about%20the%20dairy-bovine%20slaughter%20continuum%2C%20can%20excuse%20themselves%20from%20having%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20violence%20against%20bovines%2C%20and%20can%20target%20the%20slaughter%20end%20of%20milk%20production%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98cruel%20act%E2%80%99%20of%20Muslims%20and%20Dalits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChapter%205%20probes%20gaurakshaks%20and%20cow%20vigilante%20groups%2C%20revealing%20how%20their%20total%20belief%20in%20acts%20of%20violence%20to%20protect%20cows%20is%20rooted%20in%20their%20unwavering%20belief%20that%20cow%20is%20mother%20for%20Hindus.%20Narayanan%20is%20spot%20on%20when%20she%20writes%20how%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98The%20objectification%20of%20female%20and%20feminized%20Hindu%20bodies%20as%20mothering%20bodies%2C%20whether%20human%2C%20cows%2C%20or%20the%20physical%20%2F%20metaphorical%20landscape%20of%20Mother%20India%2C%20is%20a%20crux%20upon%20which%20Hindutva%20is%20founded.%20The%20erasure%20of%20bodily%20autonomy%20endured%20by%20Human%20female%20humans%2C%20becomes%20mapped%20onto%20the%20%E2%80%98dairy%E2%80%99%20cows%20and%20onto%20the%20concept%20of%20Mother%20India.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3EHindutva%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20idea%20that%20this%20feminised%20multispecies%20landscape%20of%20Hindu%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Emothers%2C%20sisters%2C%20daughters%20and%20cows%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0must%20be%20protected%20by%20Hindu%20men%2C%20from%20%E2%80%98the%20Muslim%E2%80%99%20who%20is%20a%20potential%20%E2%80%98rapist%E2%80%99%20and%20cow%20slaughterer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114358%2Flyndsay-abel-o0VdaQe5cqI-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cow%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114358%2Flyndsay-abel-o0VdaQe5cqI-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114358%2Flyndsay-abel-o0VdaQe5cqI-unsplash-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114358%2Flyndsay-abel-o0VdaQe5cqI-unsplash-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673146%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Lyndsay%20Abel%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EHindutva%20employs%20the%20same%20gendered%20entity%20to%20racialise%20Muslims%20as%20beef%20eaters%20and%20rapists%20who%20violate%20Hindu%20cows%20and%20Hindu%20women%2C%20and%20are%20thus%20treated%20as%20the%20primary%20threat%20to%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20men%E2%80%99s%E2%80%99%20property%2C%20where%20the%20trauma%20of%20violation%20to%20women%20and%20cows%2C%20is%20less%20than%20the%20trauma%20that%20this%20violation%20presents%20to%20the%20men%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20honour.%20This%20perceived%20Hindutva%20%E2%80%98dishonour%E2%80%99%20to%20a%20Hindu%20male%20justifies%20for%20the%20Hindu%20right%20the%20violence%20they%20perpetrate%20against%20marginalised%20Muslims%20and%20Dalits%2C%20employed%20in%20the%20slaughter%20end%20of%20dairy%20production%2C%20as%20slaughter%20is%20framed%20as%20a%20moral%20offence%20to%20the%20milk-consuming%20and%20cow-loving%20Hindu%20and%20cow%20worshipping%20Hindu%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20security%20is%20another%20reason%20that%20lures%20young%20men%20to%20become%20gaurakshaks%2C%20and%20genuine%20love%20for%20animals%20is%20a%20reason%20for%20some.%20The%20right%20wing%20governments%E2%80%99%20use%20of%20science%20and%20technology%20to%20test%20and%20detect%20cow%20beef%20via%20mobile%20forensic%20labs%20has%20fuelled%20the%20lynching%20of%20Dalits%20and%20Muslims.%20Recognising%20the%20rise%20of%20beef%20festivals%20celebrated%20by%20Dalit%20student%20bodies%20and%20Muslim%20communities%20as%20a%20retaliation%20against%20Hindutva%20beef%20politicisation%20and%20Hinduism%E2%80%99s%20politics%20of%20discrimination%20against%20Dalits%2C%20she%20argues%20for%20human%20rights%20and%20animal%20rights%20groups%20to%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eacknowledge%20human%20and%20animal%20vulnerabilities%20as%20morally%20relevant%2C%20and%20work%20together%20respectively%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20for%20animal%20and%20subaltern%20human%20liberation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20faced%20by%20animal%20rights%20activists%20in%20under-resourced%20countries%2C%20their%20attempts%20to%20rescue%20and%20shelter%20animals%2C%20and%20the%20choices%20they%20have%20to%20make%20between%20overcrowded%20shelters%2C%20turning%20animals%20away%20or%20using%20them%20as%20milk%20or%20traction%20animals%2C%20is%20analysed%20herein.%20She%20flags%20how%20the%20movement%20in%20not%20having%20a%20unified%20politics%20for%20all%20animals%2C%20accompanied%20by%20inconsistent%20messaging%20often%20focusing%20only%20on%20cows%2C%20are%20indistinguishable%20from%20Hindu%20right-wing%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChapters%206%20details%20the%20brutality%20and%20suffocation%20during%20transportation%2C%20illegal%20trafficking%20and%20the%20butcher-vigilante-police%20informer%20networks%20that%20serve%20both%20cow%20transporters%20and%20cow%20vigilantes.%20Chapter%207%20describes%20the%20horror%20chambers%20of%20animal%20slaughter%2C%20as%20animals%20await%20their%20death%20in%20industrial%2C%20municipal%20and%20backyard%20underground%2Fillegal%20slaughter%20spaces.%20In%20these%20chapters%20she%20also%20vividly%20describes%20the%20brutalising%20impact%20this%20has%20on%20the%20humans%20who%20people%20the%20process%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20whom%20belong%20to%20Dalit%2C%20Muslim%20and%20oppressed%20OBC%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20concludes%20her%20book%20offering%20veganism%20and%20a%20vegan%20food%20economy%20as%20the%20alternative%20to%20animal-based%20food%20regimes%2C%20arguing%20this%20will%20at%20once%20(i)%20end%20all%20forms%20of%20violence%20and%20exploitation%20of%20animals%2C%20(ii)%20completely%20halt%20the%20environmental%20degradation%20resulting%20from%20animal-agriculture%2C%20(iii)%20contribute%20to%20climate%20resilience%20as%20it%20does%20away%20with%20methane%20from%20animals%2C%20(iv)%20ensure%20sustainable%20vegan%20food%20production%20as%20farmer%20livelihoods%20and%20(v)%20counter%20Brahminism%20and%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20veterinary%20scientist%20and%20food%20sovereignty%20activist%2C%20who%20has%20spent%20the%20last%2037%20years%20of%20my%20professional%20life%20living%20and%20working%20with%20Adivasi%2C%20Dalit%2C%20Vimukta%20jati%20and%20other%20OBC%20and%20Muslim%20landless%2C%20small%20and%20marginal%20food%20producers%20whose%20livelihoods%20vitally%20include%20and%20depend%20on%20animals%2C%20in%20rural%20and%20indigenous%20territories%20in%20the%20states%20of%20Telangana%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffoodsovereigntyalliance.wordpress.com%2F2017%2F10%2F15%2Fthe-milk-crisis-in-india-the-story-behind-the-numbers%2F%5C%22%3Econsistently%20critiqued%20the%20growth%20of%20capitalist%20animal-agriculture%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20also%20called%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fsagari-r-ramdas%5C%22%3EBrahminism%20and%20Hindu%20right-wing%20politics%20for%20their%20animal%20slaughter%20politics%20which%20ignore%20the%20logical%20continuum%20of%20dairying%20and%20beef%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20commend%20Narayanan%20for%20her%20important%20expos%C3%A9%20of%20the%20cruelty%20entrenched%20within%20industrialised%20capitalist%20Indian%20dairy%20animal-agriculture%20system%20and%20how%20it%20is%20advanced%20and%20supported%20by%20Hindutva%20bovine%20politics%20and%20the%20hypocrisy%20of%20Brahminism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20I%20differ%20deeply%20with%20her%20analysis%20is%20her%20uncritical%20and%20academically%20non-rigorous%20(or%20is%20it%20privileged%20bias)%20and%20crude%20lumping%20together%20of%20all%20forms%20of%20animal-agriculture%20as%20being%20essentially%20exploitative%20and%20based%20on%20a%20violent%2C%20cruel%20and%20dominating%20relationship%20between%20humans%20and%20animals.%20By%20tracing%20and%20locating%20the%20history%20of%20animal%20rearing%20to%20either%20its%20Vedic%20interpretations%20or%20the%20World%20Bank-shaped%20Operation%20flood%20Dairy%20Development%20Indian%20experience%2C%20she%20has%20completely%20undermined%2C%20dismissed%20and%20excluded%20the%20subaltern%20histories%20and%20powerful%20agency%20of%20non-industrialised%2C%20non-capitalist%2C%20non-extractivist%20and%20non-brahminical%2C%20animal%20rearing%20worldviews%2C%20livelihoods%2C%20food%20cultures%20and%20practices%20of%20caste%20oppressed%20Dalit-Bahujan-Muslim%20and%20Adivasi%20communities%2C%20and%20yes%20the%20loving%20relationships%20they%20have%20nurtured%20with%20their%20animals.%20These%20have%20evolved%20over%20generations%2C%20of%20careful%20selection%2C%20breeding%20(not%20the%20breeding%20she%20sees%20in%20modern%20day%20dairy%20farms)%2C%20feeding%2C%20healing%20and%20caring%20of%20their%20animals%20and%20associated%20environments%2C%20to%20live%20well%20in%20specific%20ecologies%2C%20and%20for%20definite%20usages%2Fpurposes%20%E2%80%93%20a%20term%20Narayanan%20would%20undoubtedly%20interpret%20as%20embodied%20violence%3B%20and%20yet%20even%20up%20until%20as%20late%20as%20the%20early%201990s%20which%20heralded%20the%20onset%20of%20liberalisation%20and%20outright%20capitalist%20growth%20in%20India%2C%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20Indian%20milk%20markets%20were%20outside%20the%20realm%20of%20the%20organised%20and%20industrialising%20frontiers%20of%20dairying%2C%20and%20up%20until%20the%20early%201980s%2C%2075%25%20of%20energy%20in%20Indian%20farming%20came%20from%20draught%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20these%20systems%20of%20animal%20rearing%20livelihoods%2C%20calves%20are%20not%20separated%20from%20their%20mothers%3B%20cows%2C%20buffaloes%2C%20pigs%2C%20goats%2C%20sheep%2C%20poultry%2C%20yak%2C%20camels%20are%20not%20subjected%20to%20the%20cruelty%20witnessed%20and%20discussed%20in%20factory%20farmed%20animals.%20Male%20animals%20breed%20naturally%20with%20females%2C%20and%20are%20not%20%E2%80%98milked%E2%80%99%20for%20semen.%20Male%20calves%20are%20not%20starved%20and%20discarded%20as%20worthless%2C%20because%20they%20historically%20were%20the%20basis%20of%20food%20farming%20and%20transportation%2C%20and%20yes%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20adult%20males%2C%20and%20females%20which%20finally%20stopped%20calving%2C%20were%20also%20and%20always%20consumed%20as%20food.%20Meat%20was%20never%20consumed%20every%20day%2C%20but%20on%20special%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustrialising%2C%20capitalising%20and%20brahminising%20livestock%20policies%20in%20India%20beginning%20from%20the%201970s%20onwards%2C%20and%20fast-tracked%20since%20the%20past%2030%20years%2C%20have%20proactively%20and%20aggressively%20facilitated%20the%20%E2%80%98specialisation%E2%80%99%20of%20production%20(dairying%20in%20bovines%20and%20meat%20in%20goats%20and%20sheep%2C%20for%20instance)%2C%20displacing%20the%20holistic%20multifunctional%20%E2%80%98non-mother%20cow%E2%80%99%20role%20of%20animals%20in%20people%E2%80%99s%20livelihoods.%20What%20Narayanan%20overlooks%20is%20how%20the%20aggressive%20spurt%20in%20industrialisation%20and%20capitalisation%20of%20dairying%20post%20liberalisation%20displaced%20over%20five%20million%20small%20and%20marginal%20farmers%20from%20dairying%20between%202000%20and%202016.%20As%20dairying%20specialised%2C%20industrialised%20and%20has%20got%20%E2%80%98organised%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20small%20farmers%20mostly%20Dalit-Bhaujan%20and%20Muslim%2C%20have%20been%20replaced%20by%20larger%20and%20larger%20specialised%20dairy%20farmers%20who%20are%20%E2%80%98higher%20up%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20hierarchy%20of%20caste%2C%20and%20projections%20are%20that%20farm%20sizes%20will%20only%20increase%20with%20increased%20intensification.%20Unfortunately%2C%20animal%20rights%20activists%2C%20including%20Narayanan%2C%20will%20find%20any%20kind%20of%20utilitarian%20role%20of%20domesticated%20animals%20%E2%80%93%20even%20in%20their%20non-industrialised%20multifunctional%20forms%20%E2%80%93%20as%20providers%20of%20energy%2C%20draught%2C%20transportation%2C%20milk%2C%20meat%2C%20dung%2C%20urine%2C%20leather%2C%20grazers%20to%20control%20forest%20fires%2C%20and%20disperse%20seeds%2C%20as%20an%20act%20of%20anthropocentric%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114505%2Fshruti-singh-E_sU1oqqBMw-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114505%2Fshruti-singh-E_sU1oqqBMw-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114505%2Fshruti-singh-E_sU1oqqBMw-unsplash-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114505%2Fshruti-singh-E_sU1oqqBMw-unsplash-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673147%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Shruti%20Singh%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20striving%20hard%20to%20make%20the%20case%20of%20a%20world%20free%20of%20animal%20agriculture%20being%20core%20to%20fighting%20caste%20and%20fascism%2C%20she%20attempts%20to%20downplay%20the%20importance%20of%20beef%20in%20Dalit%20cultures%2C%20attributing%20the%20assertions%20of%20beef%20as%20a%20mere%20response%20to%20Hindutva%20politics%20and%20to%20counter%20the%20wider%20landscape%20of%20discrimination.%20However%2C%20in%20doing%20so%2C%20she%20masks%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20rich%2C%20joyous%20and%20flavourful%20existence%20of%20beef%20as%20an%20intrinsic%20and%20proud%20presence%20in%20Dalit%20cultures%2C%20so%20powerfully%20and%20vividly%20captured%20for%20example%20in%20Yendluri%20Sudhakar%E2%80%99s%20collection%20of%20tales%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telugubooks.in%2Fproducts%2Fspeaking-sandals%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESpeaking%20Sandals%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%2C%20recently%20published%20in%20the%20English%20from%20its%20original%20Telugu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20proposal%20on%20veganism%20is%20full%20of%20rhetoric%2C%20and%20demonstrates%20complete%20ignorance%20of%20environmental%2C%20climatic%20and%20ecological%20realities%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20there%20are%20vast%20geographies%20of%20grasslands%20in%20India%2C%20which%20are%20most%20sustainably%20utilised%20for%20animal%20grazing%2C%20and%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20huge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F932145%2Fplanting-trees-is-a-good-idea-but-not-everywhere-especially-not-in-grasslands%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20havoc%20and%20damage%20by%20attempts%20to%20raise%20%E2%80%98trees%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20farm%20these%20grasslands.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fenvironment%2Fstory%2Fclimate-change-global-warming-animal-grazing-soil-carbon-stability-2287264-2022-10-19%5C%22%3ERecent%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20revealed%20the%20significant%20role%20of%20animal%20grazing%20in%20climate%20mitigation.%20The%20energy%20role%20of%20domestic%20animals%20in%20farming%20and%20transportation%20will%20be%20critical%20in%20a%20world%20which%20is%20soon%20nearing%20peak%20oil.%20Her%20proposals%20of%20promoting%20cashew%20trees%20to%20make%20non-dairy%20%E2%80%98cashew%20milk%E2%80%99%20is%20equally%20disturbing%20%E2%80%93%20as%20she%20is%20oblivious%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20to%20the%20violent%20destruction%20of%20forest%20shifting%20cultivation%20practices%2C%20caused%20by%20cashew%20plantations%20forcibly%20promoted%20on%20Adivasi%20territories%2C%20which%20brought%20food%20insecurity%20to%20Adivasi%20homes%2C%20and%20deprived%20their%20animals%20of%20grazing%20resources.%20Whilst%20she%20highlights%20how%20intensive%20dairying%20drains%20scarce%20water%20resources%2C%20she%20ignores%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbusiness%2F2014%2Fsep%2F14%2Falarm-almond-farmers-drain-california-dry%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCalifornian%2520farmers%252C%2520estimated%2520to%2520grow%2Cthe%2520state%2527s%2520future%2520water%2520reserves.%5C%22%3Ea%20similar%20drain%20on%20water%20resources%20in%20drought%20prone%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20milking%20water%20to%20grow%20almonds%20to%20produce%20vegan%20almond%20milk.%20She%20also%20then%20avoids%20completely%20the%20question%20of%20the%20centrality%20of%20meat%20and%20halal%20in%20Islamic%20cultures%2C%20and%20how%20this%20will%20be%20addressed%20by%20veganism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shh.mpg.de%2F1977786%2Ftaylor-sheep%5C%22%3E10%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20wild%20sheep%20were%20domesticated%20by%20humans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20meet%20human%20needs%2C%20and%20this%20history%20of%20domestication%20resulted%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20diverse%20domestic%20animals%20and%20intrinsic%20relationships%20between%20humans%20and%20animals.%20Several%20animal%20breeds%20across%20species%20have%20already%20disappeared%20in%20India%20with%20the%20emergence%20of%20exclusive%20product%20specialidation-based%20animal%20farming%20whether%20for%20only%20dairying%20or%20%E2%80%98meat%E2%80%99%2C%20pushed%20by%20industrial%20capitalist%20and%20brahminic%20animal%20agriculture%20policies.%20Veganism%20would%20mean%20the%20death%20of%20all%20domesticated%20animal%20species%2C%20as%20people%20would%20have%20no%20reason%20to%20rear%20animals%20any%20longer.%20The%20forces%20of%20industrialisation%20and%20capitalism%2C%20and%20in%20the%20case%20of%20India%2C%20Brahminism%2C%20have%20chosen%20not%20to%20pursue%20and%20invest%20in%20science%20and%20technology%20to%20develop%20ways%20in%20which%20animals%20can%20be%20%3Cem%3Eslaughtered%3C%2Fem%3E%20without%20them%20having%20to%20experience%20trauma%2C%20fear%2C%20stress%20and%20pain.%20Decriminalising%20slaughter%20is%20core%20to%20dismantling%20caste%20and%20challenge%20Brahminism%3B%20accompanied%20by%20de-growth%20and%20de-industrialising%20animal%20rearing%20policies%2C%20which%20nurture%20a%20return%20to%20multifunctional%2C%20decentralised%20and%20localised%20animal%20livelihoods%2C%20are%20together%20crucial%20to%20stop%20this%20violence%20against%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESagari%20R.%20Ramdas%20is%20a%20veterinary%20scientist%20associated%20with%20the%20Food%20Sovereignty%20Alliance%2C%20India.%20She%20can%20be%20reached%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Asagari.ramdas%40gmail.com%5C%22%3Esagari.ramdas%40gmail.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694761821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15114302%2Ftaylor-brandon-rm8qzG2Dbcc-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fyamini-narayanan-mother-cow-mother-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Yamini%20Narayanan's%20expos%C3%A9%20of%20the%20cruelty%20entrenched%20within%20the%20industrialised%20capitalist%20Indian%20dairy%20animal-agriculture%20system%20and%20how%20it%20is%20advanced%20and%20supported%20by%20Hindutva%20bovine%20politics%20is%20commendable.%20But%20her%20lumping%20together%20of%20all%20forms%20of%20animal-agriculture%20as%20being%20essentially%20exploitative%20requires%20questioning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUr