kokernag-gunfight-soldier-missing-col-manpreet-singh-maj-ashish-dhonchak-dsp-humayun-bhat%2Farticleshow%2F103677323.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20iPhone%2012%20Emitting%20Too%20Much%20Radiation%3F%20What%20We%20Know%20So%20Far%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EApple%20iPhone%2012%2C%20which%20was%20launched%20in%202020%2C%20has%20been%20embroiled%20in%20a%20controversy%20after%20allegations%20of%20radiation%20leak.%20France%20has%20asked%20the%20company%20to%20stop%20selling%20the%20gadget%20for%20emitting%20too%20much%20electromagnetic%20radiation%2C%20but%20Apple%20maintains%20that%20its%20device%20follows%20global%20radiation%20standards.%20This%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Apple%20released%20its%20latest%20device%20-%20iPhone%2015%20-%20at%20the%20Wonderlust%20event.%20The%20issue%20is%20likely%20to%20affect%20the%20sale%20of%20the%20iPhone%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Apple%20is%20already%20worried%20about%20the%20slump%20in%20the%20sales%20of%20the%20gadget%20that%20accounts%20for%20over%2080%25%20of%20its%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20allegations%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFrance%20tested%20141%20cellphones%20and%20found%20that%20when%20the%20iPhone%2012%20is%20held%20in%20a%20hand%20or%20carried%20in%20a%20pocket%2C%20its%20level%20of%20electromagnetic%20energy%20absorption%20(measure%20of%20radiation%20absorbed%20by%20a%20human%20body)%20is%205.74%20watts%20per%20kilogram%2C%20higher%20than%20the%20EU%20standard%20of%204%20watts%20per%20kilogram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Frequency%20Agency%20wants%20Apple%20to%20%26quot%3Bimplement%20all%20available%20means%20to%20rapidly%20fix%20this%20malfunction%26quot%3B%20for%20phones%20already%20in%20use%20and%20warns%20if%20that%20doesn't%20work%2C%20it%20will%20have%20to%20recall%20the%20devices%20already%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20France%20decide%20to%20test%20iPhone%2012%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EVarious%20governments%20are%20free%20to%20carry%20out%20tests%20on%20electronic%20devices%20to%20measure%20their%20safety%20levels.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20why%20iPhone%2012%20didn't%20pass%20the%20French%20agency's%20latest%20round%20of%20tests%20and%20why%20it%20was%20only%20that%20particular%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrance's%20digital%20minister%20has%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20phone's%20radiation%20levels%20are%20still%20much%20lower%20what%20than%20scientific%20studies%20warn%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Apple%20has%20been%20given%20%26quot%3Btwo%20weeks%26quot%3B%20to%20respond%2C%20minister%20Jean-Noel%20Barrot%20told%20French%20newspaper%20Le%20Parisien.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20the%20WHO%20say%20about%20radiation%20from%20phones%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20the%20energy%20emitted%20at%20the%20frequencies%20used%20by%20mobile%20phones%20is%20absorbed%20by%20the%20skin%20and%20other%20surface%20tissues%2C%20resulting%20in%20%26quot%3Bnegligible%20temperature%26quot%3B%20change%20in%20the%20brain%20or%20any%20internal%20organ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20studies%20have%20looked%20at%20how%20radiofrequency%20fields%20affect%20heart%20rates%2C%20blood%20pressure%2C%20sleep%20quality%2C%20and%20electrical%20activity%20in%20the%20brain.%20According%20to%20the%20WHO%2C%20there%20is%20no%20conclusive%20data%20to%20support%20any%20negative%20health%20consequences%20from%20exposure%20to%20radiofrequency%20fields%20at%20lower%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EApple's%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20defended%20its%20iPhone%2012%20model%20and%20said%20that%20the%20model%20was%20certified%20by%20multiple%20international%20bodies%20as%20compliant%20with%20global%20radiation%20standards.%20The%20company%20stated%20that%20they%20and%20third-party%20lab%20results%20proved%20the%20phone's%20compliance%20with%20the%20French%20agency.%20It%20said%20it%20was%20contesting%20the%20results%20of%20the%20review%20by%20Agence%20Nationale%20des%20Frequences%20and%20would%20continue%20to%20engage%20with%20it%20to%20show%20it%20is%20compliant.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694759400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fjvcln1jg_iphone-12-unsplash_625x300_15_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fis-iphone-12-emitting-too-much-radiation-what-we-know-so-far-4391848%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22France%20has%20asked%20the%20company%20to%20stop%20selling%20the%20gadget%20for%20emitting%20too%20much%20electromagnetic%20radiation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fis-iphone-12-emitting-too-much-radiation-what-we-know-so-far-4391848%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fis-iphone-12-emitting-too-much-radiation-what-we-know-so-far-4391848%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fis-iphone-12-emitting-too-much-radiation-what-we-know-so-far-4391848%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%229%20Popular%20half-siblings%20of%20Bollywood%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694759400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103663866%2Cimgsize-70776.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2F9-popular-half-siblings-of-bollywood%2Fphotostory%2F103663866.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103663866.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E9%20Popular%20half-siblings%20of%20Bollywood%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2F9-popular-half-siblings-of-bollywood%2Fphotostory%2F103663