%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20has%20the%20capacity%20to%20build%20PLA%20combat%20ships%20at%20200%20times%20the%20rate%20that%20the%20US%20can%2C%20per%20leaked%20US%20Navy%20intelligence%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Chinese%20naval%20frigate.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6503d6bd956dba001acdfe38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223614%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Chinese%20naval%20frigate.%3Cp%3ETang%20Ke%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChina's%20shipbuilding%20capacity%20has%20dwarfed%20US%20capabilities%2C%20per%20leaked%20US%20Navy%20intelligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Navy%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20the%20leaked%20material's%20authenticity%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fworld%2Fchinese-shipbuilding-capacity-over-200-times-greater-than-us-navy-intelligence-says%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20News%20Digital%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20has%20the%20world's%20largest%20navy%20and%20could%20have%20a%20fleet%20of%20440%20ships%20by%202030%2C%20per%20the%20Pentagon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20shipbuilding%20capacity%20is%20232%20times%20greater%20than%20the%20US%2C%20per%20leaked%20US%20Navy%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20leaked%20US%20Navy%20briefing%20slide%20with%20the%20information%20circulated%20online%20in%20July%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fthe-war-zone%2Falarming-navy-intel-slide-warns-of-chinas-200-times-greater-shipbuilding-capacity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20War%20Zone%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20online%20newsletter.%20The%20slide%20was%20titled%20%26quot%3BPLAN%20vs.%20USN%20Naval%20Force%20Laydown%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20appeared%20to%20be%20marked%20%26quot%3Bunclassified.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20data%20seen%20in%20the%20slide%2C%20China's%20shipyards%20have%20a%20capacity%20of%20over%2023.2%20million%20tons%2C%20more%20than%20232%20times%20greater%20than%20the%20US%20capacity%20of%20less%20than%20100%2C000%20tons.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slide%20also%20appears%20to%20contrast%20the%20%26quot%3Bbattle%20force%20composition%26quot%3B%20of%20both%20navies%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Bcombatant%20ships%2C%20submarines%2C%20mine%20warfare%20ships%2C%20major%20amphibious%20ships%2C%20and%20large%20combat%20support%20auxiliary%20ships.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20US%20Navy%20spokesperson%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fworld%2Fchinese-shipbuilding-capacity-over-200-times-greater-than-us-navy-intelligence-says%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20News%20Digital%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20article%20published%20on%20September%2014%20that%20the%20briefing%20slide%20is%20authentic.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20slide%20%26quot%3Bprovides%20context%20and%20trends%20on%20China's%20shipbuilding%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20warned%20that%20the%20Navy%20did%20not%20intend%20for%20it%20to%20be%20read%20as%20a%20comprehensive%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20dive%26quot%3B%20into%20China's%20commercial%20shipbuilding%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20slide%20was%20developed%20by%20the%20Office%20of%20Naval%20Intelligence%20from%20multiple%20public%20sources%20as%20part%20of%20an%20overall%20brief%20on%20strategic%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20been%20hard%20at%20work%20at%20bolstering%20its%20naval%20capabilities.%20The%20country%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-navy-destroyers-photos-fleet-list-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20largest%20navy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20more%20than%20355%20vessels%20in%20its%20fleet%2C%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2021%2F11%2F03%2Fchina-has-worlds-largest-navy-with-355-ships-and-counting-says-pentagon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Naval%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20from%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23321290%2F2022-military-and-security-developments-involving-the-peoples-republic-of-china.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPentagon's%202022%20annual%20report%20on%20China's%20military%20development%3C%2Fa%3E%20further%20projects%20that%20the%20Chinese%20fleet%20will%20grow%20to%20400%20ships%20by%202025%20and%20440%20ships%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20the%20US%20has%20a%20smaller%20fleet%20of%20296%20ships%2C%20per%20a%202021%20report%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fus-military-forces-fy-2022-navy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECenter%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20US%20Navy%20is%20still%20widely%20considered%20to%20be%20the%20world's%20most%20powerful.%20Then%20US%20Secretary%20of%20Defense%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fesper-china-cannot-match-us-navy-even-with-more-ships-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Esper%20said%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20even%20if%20the%20US%20were%20to%20stop%20building%20ships%2C%20it%20would%20take%20years%20for%20China%20to%20match%20the%20US%20Navy's%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEsper%20said%20this%20was%20because%20of%20the%20US%20Navy's%20depth%20of%20experience%20and%20technological%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShip%20numbers%20are%20important%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20tell%20the%20whole%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Esper%2C%20who%20was%20speaking%20at%20a%20RAND%20Corporation%20event%20in%20September%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20from%20the%20US%20Office%20of%20Naval%20Intelligence%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for