80%99s%20extension%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20later%20allowed%20him%20to%20continue%20till%20September%2015%20%E2%80%9Ctaking%20into%20consideration%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20had%20insisted%20that%20it%20was%20important%20for%20Mishra%20to%20continue%20in%20his%20post%20because%20a%20country%20review%20of%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20for%20India%20is%20currently%20underway%20%E2%80%93%20a%20claim%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-fatf-evaluation%5C%22%3Eexperts%20had%20contested%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20despite%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20assertions%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20ED%20director%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20this%20process%2C%20it%20has%20not%20named%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20successor%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Union%20home%20ministry%20official%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fcentral-government-stays-silent-on-enforcement-directorate-chief-on-term-end-eve%2Fcid%2F1966265%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20ED%20director%20was%20appointed%20according%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%2C%202003.%20The%20Union%20government%20appoints%20the%20director%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20panel%20comprising%20two%20vigilance%20commissioners%20and%20the%20secretaries%20of%20home%2C%20finance%20and%20the%20department%20of%20personnel%20and%20training%2C%20with%20the%20central%20vigilance%20commissioner%20as%20chairperson.%20The%20former%20director%20is%20also%20consulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20far%20there%20is%20no%20clarity%20on%20whether%20the%20panel%20has%20finalised%20any%20name%20for%20the%20new%20director%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20an%20order%20on%20November%2019%2C%202018%2C%20Mishra%20was%20first%20appointed%20the%20ED%20director%20for%20a%20period%20of%20two%20years.%20His%20term%20would%20expire%20in%20November%202020.%20In%20May%20that%20year%2C%20he%20reached%20the%20retirement%20age%20of%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20an%20office%20order%20on%20November%2013%2C%202020%2C%20his%20appointment%20letter%20was%20modified%20retrospectively%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20term%20of%20two%20years%20was%20altered%20to%20%E2%80%98three%20years.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202022%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justice%20L.%20Nageswara%20Rao%20upheld%20the%20extension%2C%20saying%20that%20such%20retroactive%20revisions%20are%20only%20allowed%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Crarest%20of%20rare%20cases%E2%80%9D%20but%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-supreme-court-extension%5C%22%3Eno%20further%20extension%20can%20be%20given%20to%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fed-director-tenure-extension-politically-motivated%5C%22%3ESeveral%20petitioners%20challenged%20this%202020%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20along%20with%20two%202021%20ordinances%20promulgated%20three%20days%20before%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20retirement%20date%2C%20amending%20the%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20Act%2C%201946%2C%20and%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%2C%202003.%20Bills%20from%20these%20ordinances%20led%20to%20the%20legalisation%20of%20the%20extension%20of%20tenures%20of%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%20chiefs%20for%20a%20year%20at%20a%20time%20till%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%202022%2C%20Mishra%20was%20given%20another%20extension.%20This%20third%20extension%20and%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20CVC%20Act%20were%20challenged%20afresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694752645000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F15174623%2FSKMishra_EDdirector_1