uld%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20spacecraft.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20observed%20light%20shows%20on%20Venus%20for%20many%20years%20and%20during%20that%20time%2C%20the%20most%20accepted%20explanation%20was%20lightning.%20Venus%20might%20even%20have%20more%20lightning%20than%20Earth%2C%20NASA%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fvision%2Funiverse%2Fsolarsystem%2Fvenus-20071128.html%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202007.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20new%20study%20is%20forcing%20scientists%20to%20rethink%20those%20preconceived%20notions%2C%20suggesting%20that%20Venus'%20mysterious%20flashing%20lights%20are%20actually%20meteors%20burning%20up%20in%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1029%2F2023JE007914%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Geophysical%20Research%3A%20Planets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20notes%20that%20lightning%20on%20Venus%20is%20%26quot%3Beither%20ubiquitous%2C%20rare%2C%20or%20non-existent%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20one%20interprets%20diverse%20observations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20the%20researchers%20don't%20think%20it's%20lightning%20is%20because%20of%20Venus'%20radio%20silence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Earth%2C%20one%20way%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nssl.noaa.gov%2Feducation%2Fsvrwx101%2Flightning%2Fdetection%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Severe%20Storms%20Laboratory%3C%2Fa%3E%20monitors%20storms%20is%20by%20detecting%20radio%20waves%20from%20lightning.%20But%2C%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-cassini-pictures-free-ebook-pdf-2017-9%5C%22%3ECassini%20Probe%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-parker-solar-probe-winds-flip-suns-magnetic-field-2019-12%5C%22%3EParker%20Solar%20Probe%3C%2Fa%3E%20investigated%20the%20%26quot%3Blightning%26quot%3B%20on%20Venus%20while%20flying%20by%20the%20planet%2C%20and%20neither%20detected%20radio%20signals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiguring%20out%20the%20flashes%20are%20probably%20meteors%2C%20however%2C%20took%20additional%20research.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University%20counted%20the%20number%20of%20flashes%20observed%20at%20both%20the%20Steward%20Observatory%20and%20Japan's%20Akatsuki%20orbiter.%20They%20estimated%20between%2010%2C000%20and%20100%2C000%20flashes%20per%20year%2C%20which%20aligned%20with%20potential%20meteor%20strikes%20%E2%80%94%20enough%20to%20lead%20the%20researchers%20to%20conclude%20that%20meteors%20may%20be%20the%20culprit%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2023-09-venusian-atmosphere-meteors-lightning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhys.org%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenus%20also%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvenus-gravity-wave-akatsuki-2017-1%5C%22%3Esulfuric%20acid%20clouds%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20water%20vapor%2C%20which%20may%20not%20even%20be%20capable%20of%20producing%20lightning.%20These%20factors%20could%20indicate%20that%20the%20frequent%20flashes%20aren't%20lightning%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20good%20news%20for%20future%20missions%20to%20Venus%3B%20if%20the%20flashes%20were%20lightning%2C%20it%20could%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20probes%20entering%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLightning%20is%20likely%20too%20rare%20to%20pose%20a%20hazard%20to%20missions%20that%20pass%20through%20or%20dwell%20in%20the%20clouds%20of%20Venus%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20said.%20%26quot%3BLikewise%2C%20small%20meteoroids%20burn%20up%20at%20altitudes%20of%20%E2%88%BC100%20km%2C%20roughly%20twice%20as%20high%20above%20the%20surface%20as%20the%20clouds%2C%20and%20also%20would%20not%20pose%20a%20hazard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20believe%20that%20probes%20that%20descend%20quickly%20through%20Venus'%20atmosphere%20are%20likely%20safe%2C%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fvenus-lightning-meteor-strikes-atmosphere%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22f11db25f293bf1431784af1e0063d8e4%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fvenus-lightning-meteor-strikes-atmosphere%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace.com%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spacecraft%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsolarsystem.nasa.gov%2Fplanets%2Fvenus%2Fexploration%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%221375e80dbef5f4418e2d71dad77b5199%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsolarsystem.nasa.gov%2Fplanets%2Fvenus%2Fexploration%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehasn't%20landed%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Venus%20since%20the%201980s.%20Extreme%20heat%20and%20crushing%20pressure%20make%20it%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-venus-surface-is-like-2017-1%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%2233e245ff2ce3dd902e6ed3110ef69430%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-venus-surface-is-like-2017-1%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3Every%20inhospitable%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Soviet%20Union's%20Venera%2013%20probe%20set%20the%20record%20for%20surviving%20two%20hours%20on%20the%20planet%20in%201981.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20plans%20to%20send%20the%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fssed.gsfc.nasa.gov%2Fdavinci%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%229d433214bb33a84d8426b8857267