tml%5C%22%3Ewebsite%20was%20still%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20of%20late%20Thursday%20in%20New%20York%2C%20while%20users%20have%20taken%20to%20social%20media%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FVegasIssues%2Fstatus%2F1702033954109538331%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshowcase%20some%20apparently%20inoperable%20gambling%20machines%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0at%20the%20company's%20Las%20Vegas%20location.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScattered%20Spider%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20an%20offshoot%20of%20ALPHV%2C%20a%20ransomware%20gang%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2023%2F09%2F14%2Fmgm-cyberattack-outage-scattered-spider%2F%5C%22%3ETechCrunch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20group%20claiming%20responsibility%20for%20the%20MGM%20hack%2C%20but%20denying%20any%20involvement%20with%20the%20Caesar's%20breach.%20Still%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported%20the%20group%20was%20responsible%20for%20both%20of%20the%20attacks%2C%20citing%20four%20people%20it%20said%20were%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Charles%20Carmakal%2C%20chief%20technical%20officer%20for%20Mandiant%20Inc.%2C%20a%20cyber%20defense%20company%20that%20is%20part%20of%20Google%20Cloud%2C%20posted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D51bc1d589b96e0acddfb68e5afa41e8703338c9013d57daaa2efb781d923117e%26postID%3D6503413274fcf693ad3710de%26postSlug%3Dmgm-caesars-las-vegas-casinos-targeted-scattered-spider-hacking-group-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fposts%252Fcharlescarmakal_unc3944-hospitality-entertainment-activity-7107781482470920193-XnW6%253Futm_source%253Dshare%2526utm_medium%253Dmember_desktop%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20group%20is%20comprised%20of%20many%20members%20who%20%26quot%3Bare%20native%20English%20speakers%20and%20are%20incredibly%20effective%20social%20engineers.%26quot%3B%20Some%20are%20as%20young%20as%201