https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F24214119%2Fmha.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Before%20the%20September%2030%20deadline%20for%20the%20renewal%20of%20Foreign%20Contribution%20Regulation%20Act%20(FCRA)%20licences%20for%20non-governmental%20organizations%20(NGOs)%2C%20the%20government%20has%20revoked%20the%20licences%20of%20three%20organisations%3A%20Save%20The%20Children%2C%20Srinivas%20Malliah%20Memorial%20Theatre%20Crafts%20Museum%2C%20and%20SEWA%2C%20which%20is%20involved%20in%20animal%20husbandry%2C%20dairying%2C%20and%20fisheries%20activities%20in%20North%20East%20Delhi%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fhome-ministry-cancels-fcra-licence-of-bal-trust%2Farticleshow%2F103643895.cms%3Futm_source%3Dcontentofinterest%26utm_medium%3Dtext%26utm_campaign%3Dcppst%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUK-based%20NGO%20Save%20The%20Children%E2%80%99s%20India%20unit%20Bal%20Raksha%20Bharat%E2%80%99s%20licence%20has%20been%20revoked%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20Save%20The%20Children%20disclosed%20in%20its%20audited%20report%20filed%20in%20March%20that%20it%20had%20received%20Rs%20163.18%20crore%20in%20its%20bank%20accounts%20and%20Rs%2066.66%20lakh%20worth%20of%20in-kind%20contributions%20for%20the%20year%202021-22.%20The%20prominent%20child%20rights%20group%20operates%20in%2016%20states%20across%20India.%20A%20senior%20representative%20from%20the%20organisation%20confirmed%20the%20cancellation%20of%20its%20FCRA%20licence%20to%20the%20business%20daily%2C%20but%20did%20not%20provide%20further%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20NGO%20to%20lose%20its%20FCRA%20licence%2C%20Srinivas%20Malliah%20Memorial%20Theatre%2C%20was%20established%20in%20the%20memory%20of%20Ullal%20Srinivas%20Malliah%2C%20a%20freedom%20fighter%20and%20politician.%20It%20focuses%20on%20providing%20training%20in%20traditional%20handicrafts%2C%20including%20puppet%20making%2C%20mask%20making%2C%20bamboo%20crafts%2C%20paper%20figures%2C%20toys%2C%20embroidery%2C%20tailoring%2C%20and%20needlework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENGOs%20holding%20FCRA%20licences%20are%20required%20to%20apply%20for%20licence%20renewal%2C%20with%20the%20deadline%20extended%20to%20September%2030%2C%202023%2C%20following%20amendments%20to%20the%20FCRA%20law%20introduced%20in%20September%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20prominent%20NGOs%20had%20their%20FCRA%20licences%20renewed%20during%20this%20extension%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fshah-rukh-khan-and-the-fine-art-of-managing-contradictions%5C%22%3EAs%20Three%20More%20NGOs%20Lose%20FCRA%20Licence%2C%20a%20Relook%20at%20the%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Funding%20Restrictions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%2C%20there%20are%20currently%2016%2C497%20active%20NGOs%20with%20FCRA%20licences%20in%20India%2C%20and%20348%20trusts%20have%20received%20fresh%20registrations%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20grants%20FCRA%20licences%20to%20NGOs%20for%20five%20years.%20It%20evaluates%20applications%20based%20on%20annual%20returns%20and%20foreign%20grants%20received%20for%20their%20intended%20purposes.%20Any%20misuse%20or%20diversion%20of%20foreign%20funds%20by%20NGOs%20is%20considered%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20FCRA%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20the%20ministry%20revoked%20the%20FCRA%20licence%20of%20YWCA%20Delhi%2C%20citing%20fund%20diversion.%20The%20NGO%2C%20founded%20in%201912%2C%20operates%20several%20working%20women%E2%80%99s%20hostels%20throughout%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694694604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F24214119%2Fmha.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhome-ministry-cancels-fcra-licence-of-bal-raksha-bharat-two-other-ngos%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20other%20two%20NGOs%20that%20lost%20their%20FCRA%20licence%20are%20Srinivas%20Malliah%20Memorial%20Theatre%2C%20and%20SEWA%2C%20which%20is%20involved%20in%20animal%20husbandry%2C%20dairying%2C%20and%20fisheries%20activities%20in%20North%20East%20Delhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhome-ministry-cancels-fcra-licence-of-bal-raksha-bharat-two-other-ngos%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20Allow%20the%20Govt%20to%20Decide%20Who%20Gets%20Booked%20and%20Who%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20for%20the%20Same%20Act%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F12180417%2FIMG_3931.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDecolonisation%20is%20a%20delicate%20task.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20it%20requires%20the%20difficult%20acknowledgment%20that%20there%20are%20always%20continuities%20in%20knowledge%2C%20and%20that%20the%20trick%20is%20not%20to%20be%20embarrassed%20by%20them%2C%20or%20conceal%20them%2C%20but%20rather%20to%20engage%20critically%20with%20colonial%20contributions%20to%20knowledge%2C%20and%20correct%20or%20adapt%20it%20where%20necessary%2C%20in%20order%20to%20redistribute%20power%20and%20expand%20freedoms%20in%20the%20present.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20decolonisation%20may%20also%20be%20imagined%20as%20an%20act%20of%20violent%20rupture%20from%20the%20past%2C%20where%20each%20new%20achievement%20is%20seen%20not%20as%20building%20upon%20(or%20even%20breaking%20apart)%20existing%20knowledge%20but%20as%20reconquest.%20Such%20a%20position%20views%20%E2%80%98civilisations%E2%80%99%20as%20homogenous%20and%20isolated%20blocs%20in%20time%20and%20space%2C%20and%20decolonisation%20merely%20as%20reclamation%20(and%20not%20redistribution)%20of%20lost%20power.%20There%20is%20always%20the%20risk%2C%20then%2C%20that%20the%20process%20is%20reduced%20to%20a%20%E2%80%98civilisational%E2%80%99%20show%20of%20supremacy%20and%20strength.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20the%20denial%20of%20epistemological%20and%20cultural%20continuities%20with%20the%20past%20is%20very%20much%20a%20colonial%20mode%20of%20exercising%20control.%20Moreover%2C%20such%20repudiation%20results%20either%20in%20violent%2C%20yet%20often%20meaningless%2C%20ruptures%20like%20simplistic%20rendering%20of%20histories%2C%20or%20in%20some%20cases%20complete%20erasures%20%E2%80%93%20changing%20familiar%20names%2C%20altering%20architectural%20heritage%20or%2C%20and%20often%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20also%20results%20in%20an%20unexamined%20acceptance%20of%20the%20underlying%20logic%20of%20colonialism%20which%2C%20put%20loosely%2C%20treats%20people%20as%20expendable%20to%20state%20power%20and%20profits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20seem%20to%20be%20living%20in%20such%20a%20moment%20at%20present.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20significant%20portion%20of%20state%20and%20populist%20discourse%20is%20framed%20around%20conquest%2C%20reconquest%2C%20and%20attempts%20to%20establish%20some%20sort%20of%20epistemic%20hegemony.%20We%20would%20rather%20be%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Evishwaguru%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(global%20teacher)%2C%20implying%20a%20preference%20for%20benevolent%20domination%2C%20than%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Evishwamitra%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(universal%20friend)%2C%20which%20might%20evoke%20something%20closer%20to%20decolonised%2C%20equal%20friendships.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-drafting-shoddy-sakshya-nyay-sanhita-ipc-evidence%5C%22%3EShoddy%20Drafting%20Has%20Left%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%20With%20Glaring%20Errors%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20in%20this%20moment%20that%20the%20government%20has%20introduced%20three%20new%20Bills%20in%20parliament%2C%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20repealing%20the%20%E2%80%98colonial%E2%80%99%20criminal%20laws%20comprising%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20of%201860%2C%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20and%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201898%20(reenacted%20in%201973).%20The%20new%20Bills%20are%20not%20mere%20amendments%20but%20apparently%20%E2%80%98decolonised%E2%80%99%20laws%20for%20contemporary%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20examine%20the%20continuities%20and%20the%20ruptures%20that%20are%20on%20display%20in%20the%20new%20Bills.%20It%20would%20also%20be%20worthwhile%20to%20see%20whether%20the%20attempt%20at%20%E2%80%98decolonisation%E2%80%99%20manages%20to%20redistribute%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20does%20the%20state%20organise%20power%20within%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20tasks%20that%20laws%20perform%20is%20to%20ascribe%20meanings%20to%20everyday%20acts.%20They%20organise%20cognitive%20abilities%20such%20that%20certain%20actions%20are%20collectively%20recognised%20as%20being%20criminal%2C%20and%20certain%20others%20as%20not.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaws%20also%20arrange%20and%20organise%20acceptable%20forms%20of%20violence%3A%20an%20individual%20who%20confines%20another%20against%20their%20will%2C%20in%20order%20to%20coerce%20them%20into%20doing%20something%2C%20is%20committing%20an%20offence%2C%20unlike%20the%20state%20which%20may%20hold%20a%20suspect%20for%20six%20months%20without%20charge%20as%20a%20coercive%20interrogation%20tactic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20arrangements%20of%20the%20law%20leave%20scope%20for%20inequity%20in%20the%20distribution%20of%20power%20between%20state%20and%20citizens.%20Yet%20this%20is%20tolerable%2C%20since%20there%20is%20a%20presumption%20of%20neutrality%20with%20the%20state.%20It%20is%20presumed%20that%20the%20state%20enforces%20restrictions%20only%20in%20the%20larger%20%E2%80%98public%20interest%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20does%20so%20equally%20with%20respect%20to%20different%20interest%20groups.%20The%20state%20is%20shorthand%20for%20nobility%20of%20purpose.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20are%20rebuttable%20presumptions%2C%20of%20course.%20In%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20laws%20also%20provide%20space%20for%20groups%20and%20individuals%20to%20rebut%20the%20supposed%20neutrality%20of%20the%20state%2C%20or%20to%20try%20to%20shift%20the%20meanings%20ascribed%20to%20certain%20actions%3A%20to%20make%20the%20case%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20six%20months%20of%20detention%20without%20charge%20in%20order%20to%20be%20able%20to%20interrogate%20under%20duress%20is%20unreasonable%20and%20a%20form%20of%20violence%20upon%20a%20suspect%E2%80%99s%20liberty.%20Of%20course%2C%20for%20the%20courts%20to%20recognise%20such%20detention%20by%20the%20state%20as%20any%20kind%20of%20violence%20would%20require%20a%20clear%20cognitive%20shift.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Famit-shah-misled-parliament-on-three-criminal-bills-congress%5C%22%3EAmit%20Shah%20Misled%20Parliament%20on%20Three%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20redistribution%20of%20power%20rests%20in%20such%20pulls%20and%20pushes%20over%20meaning.%20Colonial%2C%20authoritarian%20or%20majoritarian%20states%20(and%20their%20drafting%20committees)%20guard%20the%20power%20to%20assign%20meanings%20very%20jealously.%20Such%20states%20use%20both%20structural%20and%20direct%20violence%20as%20instruments%20of%20governance%20more%20frequently.%20They%20are%20more%20invested%20in%20organising%20cognitive%20abilities%20in%20a%20way%20that%20recognises%20state%20excesses%20not%20as%20violence%20but%20as%20nationalism%3B%20and%20correspondingly%2C%20all%20critique%20as%20%E2%80%9Cconspiracy%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cviolence%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%20any%20attempt%20at%20decolonisation%20of%20criminal%20laws%20must%20naturally%20engage%20with%20the%20appropriations%20of%20meanings%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20push%20backs%20%E2%80%93%20as%20they%20have%20been%20playing%20out%20on%20the%20national%20scene%20in%20all%20too%20obvious%20ways.%20I%20have%20two%20dramatic%20examples%20in%20mind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20resurgent%20state%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20meanings%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Nalini%20and%20the%20anti-CAA%20protests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20word%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99%20is%20associated%20with%20acts%20of%20spectacular%2C%20and%20generalised%20violence.%20To%20label%20an%20act%20as%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99%20is%20to%20completely%20delegitimise%20and%20to%20hollow%20it%20of%20all%20meaning%20and%20context.%20When%20an%20act%20is%20recognised%20as%20terrorism%2C%C2%A0%20it%20deserves%20no%20more%20understanding%20or%20engagement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.casemine.com%2Fjudgement%2Fin%2F5609ad65e4b014971141147f%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EState%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20through%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%2C%20CBI%2FSIT%20vs.%20Nalini%20%26amp%3B%2025%20Ors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1999)%205%20SCC%20253%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20gave%20a%20concurring%20finding%20on%20whether%20the%20assassination%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20amounted%20to%20a%20terrorist%20act.%20The%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20assassination%20was%20an%20instance%20of%20political%20violence%20but%20did%20not%20constitute%20terrorism%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20true%2C%20LTTE%20leaders%20were%20bitterly%20critical%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98India-%20Sri%20Lanka%20Accord%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20was%20signed%20on%2022-7-1987.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20The%20mere%20fact%20that%20their%20action%20resulted%20in%20the%20killing%20of%2018%20persons%2C%20which%20would%20have%20struck%20great%20terror%20in%20the%20people%20of%20India%2C%20has%20been%20projected%20as%20evidence%20that%20they%20intended%20to%20strike%20terror%20in%20the%20people.%20We%20have%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20carnage%20at%20Sriperumbudur%20had%20bubbled%20up%20waves%20of%20shock%20and%20terror%20throughout%20India.%20But%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20evidence%20that%20any%20one%20of%20the%20conspirators%20ever%20desired%20the%20death%20of%20any%20Indian%20other%20than%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%20Among%20the%20series%20of%20confessions%20made%20by%20a%20record%20number%20of%20accused%20in%20any%20single%20case%2C%20as%20in%20this%20case%2C%20not%20even%20one%20of%20them%20has%20stated%20that%20anybody%20had%20the%20desire%20or%20intention%20to%20murder%20one%20more%20person%20along%20with%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20except%20perhaps%20the%20murderer%20herself.%20Of%20course%20they%20should%20have%20anticipated%20that%20in%20such%20a%20dastardly%20action%20more%20lives%20would%20be%20vulnerable%20to%20peril.%20But%20that%20is%20a%20different%20matter%20and%20we%20cannot%20attribute%20an%20intention%20to%20the%20conspirators%20to%20kill%20anyone%20other%20than%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20contemporaneous%20destruction%20of%20the%20killer%20also.%E2%80%9D%20%5BPages%20298%2C%20300%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENalini%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ewas%20still%C2%A0%20convicted%20and%20sentenced%20for%20murder%20under%20IPC%20Sections%20302%2F34.%20However%2C%20one%20might%20argue%20that%20the%20judgement%20did%20recognise%20how%20politically%20loaded%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99%20is%2C%20and%20kept%20the%20state%20from%20classifying%20violence%20as%20such%2C%20at%20will.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F11043650%2Fharibabu-photo.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F11043650%2Fharibabu-photo.jpg%20621w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F11043650%2Fharibabu-photo-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-258994%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22414%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOne%20of%20the%20last%20photographs%20of%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20taken%20just%20before%20his%20assassination%2C%20by%20the%20freelance%20photographer%20Hari%20Babu%2C%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20tasked%20by%20the%20LTTE%E2%80%99s%20Sivarasan.%20Tanu%2C%20the%20actual%20assassin%2C%20is%20standing%20behind%20the%20girl%20in%20a%20white%20shirt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYears%20later%2C%20a%20resurgent%20state%2C%20appearing%20before%20the%20constitutional%20court%2C%20reclaimed%20the%20right%20to%20unilaterally%20delegitimise%20criticism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20judgement%20granting%20bail%20to%20Asif%20Tanha%2C%20Devangana%20Kalita%20and%20Natasha%20Narwal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewho%20had%20been%20charged%20with%20terrorist%20offences%20for%20their%20role%20in%20actively%20mobilising%20crowds%20for%20the%20anti-CAA%20protests%20%5B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2FAJB15062021CRLA392021_105447.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAsif%20Iqbal%20Tanha%20vs.%20State%20of%20NCT%20of%20Delhi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(Crl.%20A.%2039%2F2021)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%5D%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20court%20had%20suggested%20that%20the%20state%20should%20desist%20from%20%E2%80%9Cfoisting%20extremely%20grave%20and%20serious%20penal%20provisions%2C%20frivolously%20upon%20people%E2%80%9D%20%5BPage%2086%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAsif%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%5D.%20The%20state%20appealed%20the%20judgement%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%2C%20amongst%20other%20arguments%2C%20also%20made%20this%20odd%20reference%20to%20Nalini%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ecase%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-delhi-riots-case-devangana-kalita-natasha-narwal-and-asif-iqbal-tanha-175904%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20this%20judgement%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%5Bthe%20Delhi%20High%20court%20judgment%20granting%20bail%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20to%20be%20accepted%2C%20the%20lady%20who%20assassinated%20the%20prime%20minister%20is%20also%20innocent%2C%20because%20in%20her%20mind%20also%2C%20she%20was%20only%20protesting%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20admitted%20the%20appeal%20for%20hearing%20at%20a%20later%20date%2C%20but%20pending%20hearing%2C%20these%20barbs%20continue%20to%20hang%20heavy.%20This%20remark%20contains%20two%20implications%3A%20a)%20any%20bitter%20criticism%20of%20government%20action%20may%20(or%20may%20not)%20eventually%20result%20in%20assassinations%20of%20the%20leadership%2C%20and%20regardless%20of%20the%20actual%20end%20result%2C%20criticisms%20and%20public%20protests%20are%20inherently%20dangerous%20and%20constitute%20terrorist%20activities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F04121000%2Fpinjra.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F04121000%2Fpinjra.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F04121000%2Fpinjra-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F04121000%2Fpinjra-1024x511.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F04121000%2Fpinjra-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-458469%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENatasha%20Narwal%20and%20Devangana%20Kalita.%20Photos%3A%20Twitter%2F%40SfiZhdc%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECivil%20disobedience%20and%20criminal%20misdemeanours%20form%20a%20slippery%20slope%20towards%20political%20assassinations%20and%20must%20be%20treated%20as%20one%20of%20a%20series%20of%20conspiratorial%20terrorist%20activities.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20state%20regards%20only%20those%20political%20acts%20that%20are%20critical%20of%20it%20as%20dangerous%3B%20ugly%20and%20violent%20protests%20against%20its%20dissidents%2C%20performed%20by%20its%20allies%2C%20are%20not%20delegitimised%3B%20nor%20is%20%E2%80%98reactionary%E2%80%99%20violence%20by%20the%20state%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20when%20apparently%20%E2%80%98provoked%E2%80%99%20by%20dissident%20protests%20(thus%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98goli%20maaro%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20escaped%20censure).%20Secondly%2Cwhen%20described%20as%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99%2C%20even%20a%20speech%20or%20acts%20of%20civil%20disobedience%20are%20deemed%20to%20be%20inherently%20violent%20and%20illegitimate.%20The%20state%20wishes%20to%20dispense%20with%20the%20legal%20requirement%20to%20find%20causal%20links%20between%20such%20political%20acts%20and%20actual%20instances%20of%20violence%20(caused%20by%20the%20same%20actors%20or%20with%20their%20tacit%20support).%20Note%20that%20even%20in%20Nalini%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20ruled%20that%20even%20an%20assassination%20was%20not%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eper%20se%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20terrorist%20act%20(that%20it%20was%20not%20without%20political%20meaning%20and%20context)%20and%20also%20that%20Nalini%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ecomplicity%20in%20the%20actual%20violence%20had%20to%20be%20carefully%20proven.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20new%20position%20is%20not%20borne%20out%20in%20existing%20law%2C%20particularly%20now%20after%20the%20latest%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20in%20the%20case%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F575-vernon-v-state-of-maharashtra-28-jul-2023-483922.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVernon%20Gonsalves%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20v.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EState%20of%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3E(July%2C%202023)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhere%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20after%20a%20long%20gap%2C%20insisted%20on%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eprima%20facie%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ematerial%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20link%20%E2%80%93%20as%20opposed%20to%20a%20political%20or%20rhetorical%20one%20%E2%80%93%20between%20the%20condemned%20figure%20of%20the%20dissident%20and%20actual%20violence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20this%20very%20important%20judgement%20has%20been%20followed%20by%20fresh%20criminal%20complaints%20and%20arrests%2C%20as%20before.%20The%20state%20has%20even%20filed%20complaints%20against%20journalists%2C%20and%20fact-finding%20teams%20who%20blame%20the%20government%20for%20any%20violence%20on%20the%20same%20premise%20that%20any%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%20is%20itself%20mischievous%2C%20violent%20and%20illegitimate.%20The%20state%20must%20apparently%20not%20be%20censured%20or%20held%20accountable%20anymore.%20The%20reordering%20of%20%E2%80%98legitimate%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98illegitimate%E2%80%99%20violence%20has%20thus%20slowly%20been%20taking%20shape.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Balwant%20Singh%20to%20Amulya%20Leona%20and%20Akbar%20Lone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20October%2031%2C%201984%20%E2%80%93%20the%20day%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20then%20prime%20minister%20of%20India%2C%20was%20assassinated%20%E2%80%93%20two%20government%20employees%2C%20Balwant%20Singh%20and%20Bhupinder%20Singh%2C%20walked%20out%20of%20their%20offices%20in%20Chandigarh%20and%20raised%20certain%20slogans%20in%20a%20crowded%20public%20place.%20The%20prosecution%20claimed%20that%20the%20slogans%20they%20had%20raised%20included%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKhalistan%20Zindabad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERaj%20Karega%20Khalsa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(long%20live%20khalistan%2C%20Khalsa%20will%20reign)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHinduan%20Nun%20Punjab%20Chon%20Kadh%20Ke%20Chhadange%2C%20Hun%20Mauka%20Aya%20Hai%20Raj%20Kayam%20Karan%20Da%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EHindus%20will%20be%20removed%20from%20Punjab%2C%20now%20is%20the%20time%20to%20rule)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20They%20were%20immediately%20arrested%20and%20convicted%20of%20sedition%20under%20Section%20124-A%2C%20and%20also%20of%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20communities%20under%20Section%20153A.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F123425906%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20however%2C%20set%20aside%20their%20conviction%20by%20ruling%20thus%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20casual%20raising%20of%20the%20slogans%2C%20once%20or%20twice%20by%20two%20individuals%20alone%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20aimed%20at%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20hatred%20or%20disaffection%20towards%20the%20Government%20as%20established%20by%20law%20in%20India.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Some%20more%20overt%20act%20was%20required%20to%20bring%20home%20the%20charge%20to%20the%20two%20appellants%2C%20who%20are%20Government%20servants.%20The%20police%20officials%20exhibited%20lack%20of%20maturity%20and%20more%20of%20sensitivity%20in%20arresting%20the%20appellants%20for%20raising%20the%20slogans%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Raising%20of%20some%20lonesome%20slogans%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20times%20by%20two%20individuals%2C%20without%20anything%20more%2C%20did%20not%20constitute%20any%20threat%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20as%20by%20law%20established%20not%20could%20the%20same%20give%20rise%20to%20feelings%20of%20enmity%20or%20hatred%20among%20different%20communities%20or%20religious%20or%20other%20groups.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fis-the-proposed-overhaul-of-the-criminal-justice-system-decolonising-or-recolonising-the-law%5C%22%3EIs%20the%20Proposed%20Overhaul%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Justice%20System%20Decolonising%20or%20Recolonising%20the%20Law%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202020%2C%20Amulya%20Leona%2C%20then%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Famulya-leona-bail-bengaluru%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eteenager%2C%20was%20arrested%20on%20charges%20of%20sedition%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20shouting%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPakistan%20Zindabad%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(long%20live%20Pakistan)%E2%80%9D%20from%20a%20public%20stage.%20She%20was%20whisked%20off%20even%20before%20she%20could%20properly%20complete%20the%20remainder%20of%20her%20sentence%2C%20which%20included%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHindustan%20Zindabad%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elong%20live%20India)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20reference%20to%20global%20(post-colonial)%20solidarity.%20She%20remained%20in%20jail%20for%20nearly%20four%20months%20before%20she%20was%20granted%20default%20bail.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20recently%20though%2C%20the%20state%20got%20an%20endorsement%20from%20the%20constitutional%20bench%20itself.%20During%20the%20constitutional%20challenge%20to%20the%20revocation%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20the%20state%20raised%20an%20objection%20with%20regard%20to%20a%20past%20action%20of%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners.%20It%20claimed%20that%2C%20in%202018%2C%20the%20petitioner%20had%20raised%20slogans%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPakistan%20Zindabad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20State%20Assembly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20course%2C%20actions%20in%20the%20Assembly%20are%20protected%20by%20%E2%80%98parliamentary%20privilege%E2%80%99%20(Article%20194%20of%20the%20constitution)%2C%20but%20even%20otherwise%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20has%20no%20bearing%20on%20his%20rights%20to%20challenge%20the%20revocation%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law.%20However%2C%C2%A0%20the%20constitution%20bench%20took%20the%20matter%20quite%20seriously%2C%20perhaps%20even%20thinking%20that%20to%20say%20%E2%80%9CPakistan%20Zindabad%E2%80%9D%20really%20means%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHindustan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EM%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eurdabad%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(death%20to%20India)%E2%80%9D.%20If%20so%2C%20they%20neglected%20to%20regard%20another%20finding%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBalwant%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20case%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(although%20admittedly%20by%20a%20bench%20of%20lesser%20strength)%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20the%20prosecution%20case%20that%20either%20of%20the%20appellants%20had%20shouted%20the%20slogan%20%E2%80%98Hindustan%20Murdabad%E2%80%99.%20On%20what%20material%20did%20the%20learned%20Judge%20find%20that%20the%20appellants%20had%20shouted%20that%20particular%20slogan%20belies%20our%20comprehensions.%20Obviously%2C%20for%20convicting%20the%20appellants%2C%20the%20trial%20Judge%20also%20pressed%20into%20aid%20the%20allegation%20that%20the%20appellants%20had%20shouted%20%E2%80%98Hindustan%20Murdabad%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20nobody%E2%80%99s%20case.%20The%20learned%20trial%20Judge%2C%20to%20say%20the%20least%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20drawn%20upon%20his%20imagination%2C%20a%20course%20not%20permissible%20for%20a%20Court%20of%20Law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnyhow%2C%20the%20constitutional%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20now%20demanded%20from%20the%20petitioner%20an%20affidavit%20swearing%20allegiance%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20ironically%20grants%20him%20the%20right%20to%20shout%20all%20manner%20of%20offensive%20slogans%2C%20as%20long%20as%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20cause%20immediate%20violence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F23144307%2F2020_2img20_Feb_2020_PTI2_20_2020_000166B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F23144307%2F2020_2img20_Feb_2020_PTI2_20_2020_000166B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F23144307%2F2020_2img20_Feb_2020_PTI2_20_2020_000166B-300x209.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F23144307%2F2020_2img20_Feb_2020_PTI2_20_2020_000166B-1024x714.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-436821%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22837%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAsaduddin%20Owaisi%20tries%20to%20stop%20Amulya%20Leona%20from%20shouting%20%E2%80%98Pakistan%20zindaband%2C%20Hindustan%20zindabad%E2%80%99.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20state%20has%20managed%20to%20efficiently%20attach%20the%20spectre%20of%20violence%20to%20certain%20political%20speeches%2Facts%2C%20while%20also%20removing%20any%20need%20to%20show%20actual%20violence%20in%20order%20for%20a%20speech%2Fact%20to%20be%20deemed%20%E2%80%98violent%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20time%2C%20consecutive%20governments%20first%20succeeded%20in%20attributing%20disaffection%20to%20those%20who%20shout%20%E2%80%9CPakistan%20Zindabad%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20then%20imperceptibly%20turned%20them%20into%20constitutional%20outcasts%2C%20unworthy%20of%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20committees%20speak%20only%20to%20the%20Shahs%2C%20and%20the%20Shahs%20speak%20only%20to%20God*%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202020%2C%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20appointed%20an%20all%20men%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Committee%20for%20Reforms%20in%20Criminal%20Laws%E2%80%99%20to%20review%20existing%20laws%20and%20%E2%80%98recommend%20reforms%20in%20a%20principled%2C%20effective%20and%20efficient%20manner%E2%80%99.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Committee%20came%20out%20with%20the%20draft%20Bills.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20shifts%20in%20meaning%20described%20above%20are%20recent%2C%20having%20taken%20place%20after%20the%20new%20Bills%20were%20drafted%2C%20but%20the%20small%20pushes%20have%20been%20taking%20place%20for%20years%20now.%20While%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20reaffirmed%20that%20fundamental%20rights%20cannot%20be%20suspended%20in%20principle%2Cin%20the%20case%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJustice%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fright-privacy-fundamental-right-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EK.S.Puttaswamy%20(retired)%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3E(2017)%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20state%20has%20been%20finding%20exceptions%20to%20the%20general%20rule%3A%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20they%20be%20suspended%20for%20a%20very%20short%20period%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20when%20minors%20had%20to%20be%20detained%3F%20Could%20the%20right%20to%20protest%20not%20be%20suspended%20for%20three%20days%20over%20G20%2C%20when%20we%20must%20all%20put%20our%20best%20foot%20forward%3F%20Could%20we%20not%20suspend%20the%20right%20to%20liberty%20for%20%E2%80%98constitutional%20outcastes%E2%80%99%20of%20suspect%20loyalty%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E*Borrowed%20from%20the%20poem%20about%20the%20Bostonian%20oligarchs%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Boston%20Brahmins.%20A%20handful%20of%20families%20had%20acquired%20massive%20wealth%20and%20cornered%20all%20economic%20activity%2C%20partially%20by%20keeping%20all%20decision-making%20powers%20to%20themselves%2C%20and%20justifying%20it%20by%20invoking%20their%20own%20apparent%20superior%20moral%20sense%20and%20nobility%20of%20purpose.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20to%20dear%20old%20Boston%2C%20the%20land%20of%20the%20bean%20and%20the%20Cod%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhere%20the%20Lowells%20speak%20only%20to%20Cabots%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnd%20the%20Cabots%20speak%20only%20to%20God.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20could%20the%20committee%20for%20decolonisation%20of%20criminal%20laws%20miss%20these%20questions%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20only%20a%20testimony%20to%20its%20complete%20control%20over%20ascription%20of%20meanings%20that%20the%20present%20government%20is%20able%20to%20invert%2C%20or%20change%20meanings%20as%20quicksand.%20In%20its%20deft%20hands%2C%20the%20same%20acts%20are%20either%20delegitimised%2C%20or%20deemed%20completely%20legitimate.%20This%20uncertainty%20of%20meanings%20deserves%20a%20pushback%20too%2C%20for%20it%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20apply%20its%20own%20low%20standards%20of%20%E2%80%98political%20criminality%E2%80%99%20rather%20selectively%20%E2%80%93%20some%20are%20able%20to%20disavow%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20or%20make%20vitriolic%20speeches%20about%20constitutional%20values%20with%20impunity%2C%20while%20others%20aren%E2%80%99t%20able%20to%20criticise%20state%20action%20without%20being%20deemed%20treacherous%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20did%20the%20drafters%20of%20%E2%80%98decolonised%E2%80%99%20laws%20not%20engage%20with%20the%20quietly%20looming%20figure%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98political%20prisoner%E2%80%99%20in%20India%3F%20How%20did%20they%20neglect%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20death%20in%20custody%20of%20Father%20Stan%20Swamy%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20event%2C%20the%20new%20Bills%20crystallise%20the%20shifts%20in%20meaning%20that%20the%20state%20has%20ostensibly%20been%20wanting.%20The%20new%20Bills%20formalise%20much%20that%20was%20happening%20in%20the%20dark%20recesses%20of%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%2C%20or%20in%20the%20spaces%20between%20the%20pushes%20and%20the%20pushbacks%20in%20the%20constitutional%20courts.%20They%20also%20bring%20into%20the%20criminal%20justice%20mainstream%20the%20exceptionalism%20of%20%E2%80%98security%20laws%E2%80%99%20such%20as%20Armed%20Forces%20(Special%20Powers)%20Act%20(AFSPA)%20and%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20etc%20by%20heightening%20police%20powers%20in%20a%20deliberate%2C%20visual%20way%20%E2%80%93%20the%20right%20to%20use%20%E2%80%98any%20means%20necessary%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20suspect%2C%20and%20the%20new%20right%20to%20handcuff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20meanings%2C%20the%20new%20penal%20code%20Bill%20introduces%20an%20open-ended%20offence%20of%20%E2%80%98subversive%20activities%E2%80%99%3A%20it%20could%20be%20any%20political%20act%20that%20the%20state%20wishes%20to%20delegitimise.%20It%20also%20reiterates%20a%20broad%20and%20vague%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98terrorist%20acts%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20could%20cover%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20legitimate%20protests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20Bills%20introduce%20new%20substantive%20offences%20that%20again%20organise%20meanings%20and%20reorder%20violence%20in%20specific%20ways.%20Significantly%2C%20it%20recognis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ees%20mob%20lynching%20as%20a%20separate%20offence%2C%20where%20the%20motivation%20for%20violence%20is%20the%20victim%E2%80%99s%20identity%20alone.%20However%2C%20the%20sentence%20is%20discretionary%20and%20may%20be%20reduced%20to%20seven%20years%2C%20which%20is%20less%20than%20a%20%E2%80%98normal%E2%80%99%20murder%20sentence%20of%20life%20imprisonment%20or%20death.%20It%20suggests%20that%20to%20lynch%20is%20bad%2C%20but%20not%20quite%20as%20bad%20as%20%E2%80%98murder%E2%80%99.%20Pointedly%2C%20the%20sentence%20for%20concealing%20one%E2%80%99s%20identity%20before%20marriage%2C%20in%20an%20approximation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Clove%20jihad%E2%80%9D%20narrative%2C%20is%20ten%20years%20(clauses%2069%20and%2080).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20Bills%20are%20actually%20quite%20colonial%20in%20the%20way%20that%20they%20give%20enhanced%20power%20to%20the%20state%20to%20assign%20meanings%20to%20words%20and%20actions%2C%20and%20also%20mechanical%20for%20having%20reproduced%20large%20parts%20of%20what%20they%20had%20set%20out%20to%20%E2%80%98decolonise%E2%80%99.%20But%2C%20to%20be%20fair%2C%20the%20new%20procedural%20code%20is%20also%20mindful%20of%20housekeeping%20challenges%20in%20the%20system%3A%20there%20is%20an%20obvious%20attempt%20to%20address%20pendencies%20and%20be%20efficient%2C%20primarily%20by%20denying%20strategic%20adjournments%20to%20parties%2C%20though%20not%20by%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20state%20to%20make%20superfluous%20arrests%2C%20which%20would%20automatically%20lessen%20the%20number%20of%20cases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20final%20analysis%2C%20the%20most%20dramatic%20rupture%20here%20is%20the%20trusty%20name-change.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20continuities%20in%20terms%20of%20consolidation%20of%20state%20power%20are%20writ%20large%20across%20the%20three%20new%20Bills%2C%20and%20more%20consequential.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshahrukh-alam%5C%22%3EShahrukh%20Alam%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20a%20lawyer%20who%20practices%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694692845000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F12180417%2FIMG_3931.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-new-criminal-bills-allow-the-govt-to-decide-who-gets-booked-and-who-doesnt-for-the-same-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20Bills%20are%20actually%20quite%20colonial%20in%20the%20way%20that%20they%20give%20enhanced%20power%20to%20the%20state%20to%20assign%20meanings%20to%20words%20and%20actions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-new-criminal-bills-allow-the-govt-to-decide-who-gets-booked-and-who-doesnt-for-the-same-act%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nationwide%20power%20outage%20in%20Nigeria%20as%20country%20suffers%20'total%20system%20collap