-madan-lal-to-deliver-opening-address%2Farticleshow%2F103664605.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Has%20the%20Indian%20G20%20Presidency%20Addressed%20the%20Global%20South's%20Economic%20Challenges%20and%20Priorities%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08143019%2FScreenshot-2023-09-08-at-2.29.40-PM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20G20%20Presidency%20was%20significant%20as%20it%20helped%20the%20country%20rediscover%20its%20true%20identity%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20after%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20happened%20on%20the%20day%20that%20India%20took%20over%20the%20Presidency%20of%20the%20G20%20on%20December%201%2C%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoes.gov.in%2Fg20-india-2023%2Fmoes-g20%3Flanguage_content_entity%3Den%5C%22%3Ewhen%3C%2Fa%3E%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20sent%20out%20a%20strong%20political%20message%20that%20%E2%80%9Cour%20G20%20priorities%20will%20be%20shaped%20in%20consultation%20not%20only%20with%20our%20G20%20partners%20but%20also%20with%20our%20fellow-travelers%20in%20the%20global%20South%2C%20whose%20voice%20often%20goes%20unheard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prime%20minister%20repeatedly%20highlighted%20the%20need%20to%20address%20the%20aspirations%20and%20concerns%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cglobal%20South%E2%80%9D.%20India%20almost%20positioned%20itself%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20global%20South%20it%20once%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffive-keys-takeaways-from-the-g20-summit-in-delhi%5C%22%3Eleadership%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20more%20evident%2C%20especially%20through%20its%20successful%20efforts%20to%20secure%20permanent%20membership%20for%20the%2055-member%20African%20Union%20(AU).%20The%20induction%20of%20AU%20was%20the%20most%20significant%20step%20that%20the%20G20%20countries%20have%20taken%20through%20the%20first%20expansion%20of%20the%20grouping%20since%20it%20was%20formed%20as%20a%20finance%20ministers%E2%80%99%20forum%20in%201999%20and%20was%20later%20upgraded%20in%202008%20for%20the%20summit-level%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAU%E2%80%99s%20presence%20on%20the%20high%20table%20implies%20that%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20countries%20would%20be%20able%20to%20directly%20hear%20the%20concerns%20of%20some%20of%20the%20poorest%20countries%20that%20have%20been%20steeped%20in%20external%20debt%20problems%20that%20almost%20seem%20intractable.%20Forty%20of%20the%2055-member%20AU%20receive%20support%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20under%20the%20Poverty%20Reduction%20and%20Growth%20Facility%20(PGRT)%2C%20which%20lends%20to%2070%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20poorest%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EG20%20is%20currently%20addressing%20the%20debt%20problems%20of%20heavily%20indebted%20countries.%20Two%20items%20on%20its%20agenda%20have%20been%20particularly%20important%20in%20this%20context.%20First%2C%20lowering%20the%20debt%20burden%20of%20the%2070%20low-income%20countries%20receiving%20PGRT%20support%2C%20and%20second%2C%20urgently%20reforming%20the%20multilateral%20development%20banks%20(MDBs)%20so%20as%20to%20enable%20these%20institutions%20to%20provide%20concessional%20finance%20to%20the%20low-income%20countries%2C%20including%20for%20responding%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAddressing%20the%20limitations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20India%E2%80%99s%20G20%20Presidency%20strongly%20advocated%20for%20addressing%20the%20debt%20problems%20of%20highly%20indebted%20countries%2C%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Declaration%20fell%20short%20of%20expectations.%20It%20failed%20to%20correct%20the%20shortcomings%20of%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20previous%20initiatives%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20initially%20supported%20the%20World%20Bank-IMF%20led%20Debt%20Service%20Suspension%20Initiative%20(DSSI)%20for%20temporarily%20suspending%20debt%20service%20payments%20of%20low-income%20countries%20and%20then%20adopted%20the%20%E2%80%9CCommon%20Framework%20for%20Debt%20Treatments%20beyond%20the%20DSSI.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Indian%20Presidency%20aimed%20to%20convince%20the%20G20%20to%20adopt%20a%20fresh%20approach%20toward%20addressing%20the%20debt%20issues%20of%20low-income%20countries%20by%20addressing%20the%20three%20limitations%20of%20the%20existing%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Common%20Framework%E2%80%99%20only%20covers%20debt%20owed%20by%20low-income%20countries%20to%20bilateral%20official%20creditors%20and%20excludes%20debt%20owed%20to%20multilateral%20development%20banks%20(MDBs)%2C%20while%20private%20creditors%20can%20voluntarily%20join%20the%20initiative.%20This%20approach%20falls%20short%20because%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%202019%2C%20low-income%20countries%20owed%20only%2025%25%20of%20their%20total%20outstanding%20external%20debt%2C%20and%20their%20debt%20to%20private%20creditors%20had%20surged%20from%20just%20under%20%2414%20billion%20in%202010%20to%20over%20%2483%20billion%20a%20decade%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Common%20Framework%E2%80%99%20initially%20overlooked%20the%20severe%20debt%20problems%20of%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20Pakistan.%20Although%20a%20small%20step%20was%20taken%20during%20the%20Indian%20Presidency%20to%20address%20the%20timely%20resolution%20of%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20debt%20situation%2C%20but%20extending%20the%20%E2%80%98Common%20Framework%E2%80%99%20to%20these%20countries%20would%20provide%20limited%20assistance%2C%20as%20bilateral%20official%20donors%20held%20a%20relatively%20smaller%20share%20of%20their%20accumulated%20debt.%20For%20example%2C%20in%202021%2C%20Pakistan%20owed%2030%25%20of%20its%20debt%20to%20bilateral%20official%20donors%2C%20while%20Sri%20Lanka%E2%80%99s%20corresponding%20figure%20was%20lower%20at%2020.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Common%20Framework%E2%80%99%20suffered%20from%20poor%20buy-in%20from%20potential%20beneficiaries.%20Only%20four%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Chad%2C%20Ethiopia%2C%20Zambia%2C%20and%20Ghana%20%E2%80%93%20have%20requested%20debt%20restructuring%2C%20and%20creditor%20committees%20established%20to%20find%20solutions%20are%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20such%20terms%20being%20offered%20to%20the%20debtors%2C%20even%20the%20then%20World%20Bank%20president%20David%20Malpass%20was%20critical%20of%20the%20first%20agreement%20reached%20under%20the%20%E2%80%98Common%20Framework%E2%80%99%2C%20involving%20Chad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMalpass%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fchad-debt-world-bank-idUSKBN2S1202%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20agreement%20reached%20by%20the%20creditors%20provides%20no%20immediate%20debt%20reduction.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20debt%20service%20burden%20of%20Chad%20remains%20heavy%20and%20is%20crowding%20out%20priority%20expenditures%20on%20food%2C%20health%2C%20education%20and%20climate%E2%80%9D.%20Malpass%E2%80%99s%20criticism%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Common%20Framework%E2%80%99%20was%20quite%20appropriate%20as%20he%20wanted%20to%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20G20%20initiative%20is%20not%20designed%20to%20provide%20any%20meaningful%20relief%20to%20the%20debtors%3B%20it%20only%20ensures%20that%20they%20remain%20solvent.%20In%20effect%2C%20this%20initiative%20has%20created%20a%20window%20to%20ensure%20that%20even%20in%20the%20face%20of%20severe%20economic%20stress%2C%20the%20low-income%20countries%20are%20able%20to%20meet%20their%20debt-service%20obligations%2C%20preventing%20a%20repeat%20of%20the%20events%20following%20the%201980s%20debt%20crisis%20when%20highly%20indebted%20countries%20experienced%20a%20%E2%80%9Clost%20decade%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReforming%20the%20MDBs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReforming%20the%20MDBs%20is%20closely%20linked%20to%20addressing%20the%20problems%20of%20the%20debt-stricken%20countries.%20These%20countries%20need%20access%20to%20concessional%20finance%20for%20meeting%20their%20development%20needs.%20They%20also%20need%20that%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20challenge%20of%20realising%20the%20net-zero%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20countries%2C%20with%20the%20momentum%20provided%20by%20the%20Italian%20Presidency%2C%20have%20been%20addressing%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20MDBs%20to%20meet%20their%20financing%20commitments.%20The%20Italian%20Presidency%20had%20instituted%20an%20Independent%20Review%20of%20MDBs%E2%80%99%20Capital%20Adequacy%20Frameworks%20for%20assessing%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20banks%20to%20meet%20their%20financial%20obligations.%20This%20independent%20review%20addressed%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20potential%20of%20the%20MDBs%20can%20be%20unlocked%20to%20meet%20the%20financial%20needs%20of%20the%20recipients%20without%20being%20adversely%20affected%20by%20%E2%80%9Crating%E2%80%9D%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Presidency%20took%20the%20next%20logical%20step%20to%20develop%20an%20agenda%2C%20based%20on%20which%20the%20MDBs%20can%20continue%20financing%20the%20recipients.%20This%20task%20was%20entrusted%20to%20an%20International%20Expert%20Group%20(IEG)%2C%20which%20was%20established%20to%20%E2%80%9Caddress%20the%20shared%20global%20challenges%20of%20the%2021st%20century%E2%80%9D.%20In%20its%20major%20recommendations%2C%20the%20IEG%20asked%20the%20MDBs%20to%20provide%20rapid%20and%20automatic%20concessional%20international%20assistance%20to%20countries%2C%20including%20middle-income%20countries%20hit%20by%20major%20natural%20disasters.%20The%20banks%20were%20also%20asked%20to%20change%20their%20approach%20to%20partnering%20with%20the%20private%20sector%20by%20working%20systematically%20with%20the%20private%20sector%20in%20sovereign%20and%20non-sovereign%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20IEG%20do%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20future%20prospects%20of%20concessionary%20lending%20from%20the%20MDBs%2C%20given%20that%20the%20donor%20countries%E2%80%99%20pledge%20for%20the%20latest%20three-year%20cycle%20of%20International%20Development%20Association%20funding%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.lse.ac.uk%2Finternationaldevelopment%2F2021%2F11%2F16%2Fwhat-next-for-ida%2F%5C%22%3EIDA20%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20the%20soft%20lending%20arm%20of%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20was%20well%20below%20expectations.%20This%20also%20brings%20into%20serious%20question%20the%20MDBs%E2%80%99%20ability%20to%20provide%20debt%20relief%20to%20the%20countries%20that%20are%20the%20worst%20affected%20by%20debt%20overhang%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20limits%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20debt-distressed%20countries%20to%20invest%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20that%20the%20IDA20%20faces%20is%20not%20unexpected%20since%20the%20US%20remains%20unwilling%20to%20contribute%20towards%20increasing%20the%20capacity%20of%20the%20MDBs%20to%20lend%20more.%20US%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Janet%20Yellen%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20at%20the%20third%20meeting%20of%20the%20G20%20finance%20ministers%20and%20central%20bank%20governors%20gave%20a%20clear%20indication%20when%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhome.treasury.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fjy1620%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20G20%20must%20only%20explore%20capital%20increases%20after%20the%20%5BMDB%5D%20reforms%20%E2%80%A6%20have%20progressed%20further%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20India%20was%20in%20the%20vanguard%20of%20nations%20seeking%20a%20more%20equitable%20multilateral%20trading%20regime%2C%20especially%20since%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20millennium.%20However%2C%20for%20over%20a%20decade%20now%2C%20the%20dynamics%20of%20the%20WTO%20has%20shifted%20completely%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20advanced%20countries%20who%20have%20sounded%20a%20death%20knell%20to%20multilateralism%20by%20initiating%20negotiations%20on%20issues%20of%20their%20interest%2C%20bypassing%20the%20views%20of%20the%20majority%20in%20the%20institution.%20These%20negotiations%20have%20already%20seen%2067%20members%20(out%20of%20the%20164%20members)%20agreeing%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeclaration%E2%80%9D%20on%20services%20domestic%20regulation%2C%20while%20the%20stage%20is%20being%20set%20for%20concluding%20a%20similar%20%E2%80%9Cplurilateral%E2%80%9D%20agreement%20on%20e-commerce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20country%20rightly%20opposing%20these%20negotiations%2C%20India%2C%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20G20%2C%20had%20the%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20work%20with%20the%20fellow%20travelers%20in%20the%20global%20South%20to%20initiate%20the%20steps%20towards%20preventing%20the%20degeneration%20of%20the%20WTO%20into%20a%20rich%20man%E2%80%99s%20club.%20The%20pressures%20on%20the%20countries%20in%20the%20South%20is%20squarely%20being%20felt%20by%20India%2C%20which%20has%20been%20reflected%20in%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Declaration%2C%20the%20G20%20countries%20have%20committed%20not%20to%20%E2%80%9Cimpose%20export%20prohibitions%20or%20restrictions%E2%80%9D%20on%20agricultural%20products%2C%20which%20implies%20that%20India%20is%20now%20under%20a%20moral%20obligation%20to%20maintain%20its%20exports%20of%20agricultural%20products%20even%20if%20domestic%20supply%20shortages%20result%20in%20runaway%20food%20price%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20most%20intriguing%20aspect%20of%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration%20was%20that%20despite%20the%20strong%20commitments%20for%20addressing%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20that%20were%20heard%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Summit%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9CGlobal%20South%E2%80%9D%20was%20not%20mentioned%20even%20once.%20This%20may%20not%20appear%20surprising%20given%20that%20G7%E2%80%99s%20anathema%20for%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9CSouth%E2%80%9D%20is%20quite%20well-known%20and%20G20%E2%80%99s%20progression%20under%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20politically%20powerful%20grouping.%20But%20more%20significantly%2C%20absence%20of%20any%20mention%20of%20%E2%80%9CGlobal%20South%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Declaration%20may%20well%20be%20an%20indication%20that%20the%20process%20of%20%E2%80%98G7-isation%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20G20%20is%20now%20complete.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694691054000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08143019%2FScreenshot-2023-09-08-at-2.29.40-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhas-the-indian-g20-presidency-addressed-the-global-souths-economic-challenges-and-priorities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20December%201%2C%202022%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20had%20sent%20out%20a%20strong%20political%20message%20that%20%26quot%3Bour%20G20%20priorities%20will%20be%20shaped%20in%20consultation%20not%20only%20with%20our%20G20%20partners%20but%20also%20with%20our%20fellow-travelers%20in%20the%20global%20South%2C%20whose%20voice%20often%20goes%20unheard.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhas-the-indian-g20-presidency-addressed-the-global-souths-economic-challenges-and-priorities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20may%20cut%20market%20borrowing%20if%20small%20savings%20shoot%20up%3A%20Ajay%20Seth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694691033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F05%2Ffull%2F1693935906-7325.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-may-cut-market-borrowing-if-small-savings-shoot-up-ajay-seth-123091400741_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20has%20projected%20gross%20market%20borrowing%20at%2015.43%20trn%20Indian%20rupees%20(%24185.