When%20we%20told%20them%20that%20this%20was%20their%20fee%2C%20the%20students%20slowly%20started%20bringing%20plastic%20every%20Friday%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20this%2C%20the%20founders%20came%20up%20with%20another%20path%20breaking%20solution%20to%20help%20the%20unemployment%20situation%20of%20the%20locality.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20noticed%20that%20many%20children%20started%20to%20skip%20school%20to%20do%20daily%20wage%20work.%20We%20decided%20to%20employ%20these%20kids%20in%20the%20school%20and%20pay%20them%20so%20that%20they%20would%20attend%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20Parmita%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20students%20upgrade%20to%20a%20higher%20class%2C%20we%20employ%20the%20suitable%20ones%20to%20teach%20the%20lower%20classes%20under%20supervision.%20For%20this%20service%2C%20we%20pay%20them.%20This%20way%2C%20our%20kids%20have%20the%20motivation%20to%20study%20well%20and%20become%20%E2%80%98student%20teachers%E2%80%99%20and%20earn%20pocket%20money%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20model%20helped%20them%20gain%20more%20attendance.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20the%20end%20of%202016%2C%20we%20had%20around%20200%20students%20waiting%20to%20get%20admission%20in%20the%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20model%20worked%20well%20for%20the%20school%2C%20Parmita%20observed%20that%20parents%20were%20taking%20money%20from%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20earnings%20for%20personal%20expenses%2C%20including%20buying%20liquor.%20To%20address%20this%20issue%2C%20the%20school%20decided%20to%20replace%20cash%20with%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20point%2C%20for%20example%2C%2050%20points%20represent%20Rs%2050%2C%20ensuring%20that%20the%20funds%20are%20spent%20solely%20on%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20needs.%20The%20school%20also%20partnered%20with%20local%20shops%20selling%20sweets%20and%20garments%20to%20allow%20students%20to%20use%20their%20points%20the